title: Honey Garlic Glazed Salmon
description: Tender salmon fillets coated in a sweet and savory honey garlic glaze, pan-seared to perfection. This dish combines the richness of salmon with the bold flavors of garlic and ginger for a restaurant-quality meal at home.
directions: Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper. In a small bowl, whisk together honey, soy sauce, minced garlic, and grated ginger. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place salmon skin-side up in the skillet and cook for 4 minutes. Flip salmon and brush generously with the honey garlic mixture. Cook for another 4-5 minutes, basting frequently with the glaze, until salmon is cooked through and caramelized. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve immediately with steamed vegetables or rice.

title: Mediterranean Chickpea Salad
description: A vibrant, protein-packed salad featuring chickpeas, cucumber, tomatoes, and feta in a zesty lemon dressing. This refreshing dish works perfectly as a light lunch or side dish.
directions: Drain and rinse chickpeas, then pat dry. Dice cucumber and tomatoes into bite-sized pieces. Crumble feta cheese and halve the olives. In a large bowl, combine chickpeas, cucumber, tomatoes, feta, and olives. In a small bowl, whisk together lemon juice, olive oil, oregano, salt, and pepper. Pour dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine. Let the salad sit for 10 minutes to allow flavors to meld. Garnish with fresh herbs if desired and serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: Thai Peanut Noodles
description: Chewy rice noodles tossed in a creamy peanut sauce with crisp vegetables and cilantro. This quick and flavorful dish brings the taste of Thai street food to your kitchen.
directions: Cook rice noodles according to package instructions, drain and rinse with cold water. In a bowl, whisk together peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, honey, and a splash of water until smooth. Julienne carrots and bell peppers into thin strips. In a large bowl, toss noodles with peanut sauce until well coated. Add julienned vegetables and toss again. Let sit for 5 minutes to allow flavors to combine. Garnish with chopped cilantro and crushed peanuts. Serve at room temperature or chilled with lime wedges on the side.

title: Greek Lemon Chicken Soup
description: A comforting soup with tender chicken, rice, and a silky egg-lemon sauce.
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in a large pot. Add chicken breasts and simmer for 20 minutes until cooked through. Remove chicken, shred it, and set aside. Add rice to the broth and cook for 15 minutes until tender. In a bowl, whisk eggs until frothy, then slowly whisk in lemon juice. Temper the egg mixture by slowly adding 2 cups of hot broth while whisking constantly. Remove soup from heat and slowly pour the egg-lemon mixture back into the pot, stirring continuously. Add shredded chicken and chopped dill. Season with salt and pepper and serve warm.

title: Chocolate Lava Cakes
description: Individual chocolate cakes with molten centers that flow out when broken open.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 Celsius and butter four ramekins, then dust with cocoa powder. Melt chocolate and butter together in a microwave or double boiler, stirring until smooth. In a separate bowl, whisk eggs, egg yolks, and sugar until thick and pale. Fold the chocolate mixture into the eggs, then gently fold in flour until just combined. Divide batter among prepared ramekins. Bake for 12-14 minutes until edges are firm but centers are still soft. Let cool for 1 minute, then carefully invert onto plates. Serve immediately with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: Buffalo Chicken Wings
description: Crispy chicken wings coated in tangy buffalo sauce, served with cooling blue cheese dip.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 Celsius. Pat chicken wings dry and toss with salt, pepper, and baking powder. Arrange on a wire rack over a baking sheet. Bake for 45-50 minutes, flipping halfway, until golden and crispy. Meanwhile, melt butter and mix with hot sauce. For blue cheese dip, combine crumbled blue cheese, sour cream, and a splash of milk. Toss hot wings in buffalo sauce until well coated. Serve immediately with blue cheese dip and celery sticks on the side.

title: Chicken Teriyaki Bowls
description: Grilled chicken with homemade teriyaki sauce served over rice with steamed broccoli.
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions. In a small saucepan, combine soy sauce, honey, grated ginger, minced garlic, and a splash of water. Simmer for 5 minutes until slightly thickened. Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and marinate in half the teriyaki sauce for 20 minutes. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken for 6-8 minutes until cooked through. Steam broccoli until tender-crisp. Assemble bowls with rice as base, top with chicken and broccoli, then drizzle with remaining teriyaki sauce. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.

title: Cinnamon French Toast
description: Classic breakfast with thick bread slices soaked in cinnamon-spiced egg mixture and pan-fried until golden.
directions: In a shallow bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, cinnamon, vanilla, and a pinch of salt. Heat a large skillet or griddle over medium heat and melt butter. Dip each bread slice into the egg mixture, allowing it to soak for 10 seconds per side. Place soaked bread in the hot skillet and cook for 3-4 minutes per side until golden brown and slightly crispy. Keep cooked slices warm in a low oven while finishing the rest. Serve hot with maple syrup, fresh berries, and powdered sugar.

title: Beef and Bean Chili
description: Hearty chili loaded with ground beef, kidney beans, and warming spices.
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pot over medium-high heat, breaking it into small pieces. Drain excess fat. Add diced onion and bell pepper, cook for 5 minutes until softened. Stir in chili powder, cumin, and garlic, cook for 1 minute. Add crushed tomatoes, drained kidney beans, and beef broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30-40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot with shredded cheese, sour cream, and cornbread or crackers on the side.

title: Butternut Squash Soup
description: Creamy pureed soup with roasted butternut squash and warming spices.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius. Peel and cube butternut squash, toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast for 30-35 minutes until tender and caramelized. In a large pot, saute diced onion in olive oil until soft. Add grated ginger and cook for 1 minute. Add roasted squash and vegetable broth, bring to a simmer. Use an immersion blender to puree until completely smooth. Stir in coconut milk and nutmeg. Simmer for 5 minutes and adjust seasoning. Serve hot with toasted pumpkin seeds and a drizzle of cream.

title: Greek Pasta Salad
description: Cold pasta tossed with feta, olives, tomatoes, and cucumber in a lemon vinaigrette.
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, drain and rinse with cold water. Halve cherry tomatoes, dice cucumber, and thinly slice red onion. In a large bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, cucumber, onion, sliced olives, and crumbled feta. For dressing, whisk lemon juice, olive oil, oregano, garlic, salt, and pepper. Pour dressing over salad and toss well. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving to allow flavors to develop. Garnish with fresh herbs and serve cold.

title: Chicken Enchiladas
description: Rolled tortillas filled with shredded chicken and cheese, covered in red enchilada sauce.
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius. Cook chicken in boiling water for 20 minutes until done, then shred. Mix shredded chicken with diced onion, cumin, and half the cheese. Spread quarter cup enchilada sauce in a baking dish. Fill each tortilla with chicken mixture, roll up, and place seam-side down in dish. Pour remaining enchilada sauce over tortillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake for 20-25 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve hot with sour cream, cilantro, and sliced avocado.

title: Blueberry Oatmeal
description: Creamy steel-cut oats cooked with cinnamon and topped with fresh blueberries.
directions: Bring almond milk to a boil in a medium saucepan. Stir in oats and reduce heat to low. Simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until oats are tender and creamy. Stir in cinnamon, vanilla, and maple syrup. Add half the blueberries and cook for 2 more minutes until berries start to burst. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes to thicken. Divide into bowls and top with remaining fresh blueberries, a drizzle of maple syrup, and chopped almonds if desired.

title: Pad Thai
description: Classic Thai stir-fried noodles with shrimp, peanuts, and tamarind sauce.
directions: Soak rice noodles in warm water for 30 minutes, then drain. Mix tamarind paste, fish sauce, sugar, and water for sauce. Heat oil in a wok over high heat. Cook shrimp for 2 minutes until pink, remove. Add beaten eggs and scramble. Add noodles and sauce, toss for 2 minutes. Return shrimp to wok with bean sprouts and sliced scallions. Toss everything together for 1 minute. Serve immediately topped with crushed peanuts, lime wedges, and cilantro.

title: Avocado Toast
description: Toasted sourdough topped with mashed avocado, cherry tomatoes, and everything bagel seasoning.
directions: Toast bread slices until golden and crispy. Halve avocados, remove pits, and scoop flesh into a bowl. Mash with a fork and mix in lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Spread mashed avocado generously on each toast. Halve cherry tomatoes and arrange on top. Sprinkle with red pepper flakes and everything bagel seasoning. Drizzle with olive oil if desired. Serve immediately while bread is still warm and crispy.

title: Chicken Satay
description: Grilled marinated chicken skewers served with peanut sauce.
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch strips. Mix coconut milk, curry powder, soy sauce, and honey for marinade. Add chicken and marinate for at least 2 hours. For peanut sauce, whisk peanut butter, lime juice, soy sauce, honey, and water until smooth. Thread chicken onto skewers. Grill or broil for 3-4 minutes per side until cooked through and slightly charred. Serve hot with peanut sauce, cucumber slices, and lime wedges on the side.

title: Lamb Kofta
description: Spiced ground lamb skewers grilled until charred and juicy.
directions: Finely mince onion, parsley, and garlic. In a large bowl, combine ground lamb, onion, parsley, garlic, cumin, coriander, salt, and pepper. Mix thoroughly with your hands. Divide mixture into 8 portions and shape around metal skewers into long oval shapes. Refrigerate for 30 minutes to firm up. Grill over high heat for 3-4 minutes per side until charred outside but still juicy inside. Serve with flatbread, tzatziki sauce, sliced tomatoes, and pickled vegetables.

title: Singapore Noodles
description: Curry-spiced rice noodles stir-fried with shrimp, vegetables, and eggs.
directions: Soak rice noodles in hot water for 15 minutes, then drain. Heat oil in a wok over high heat and scramble eggs, remove. Add shrimp and cook until pink, remove. Add more oil and stir-fry sliced bell pepper for 2 minutes. Add curry powder and cook for 30 seconds. Add noodles, soy sauce, and a splash of water. Toss for 2 minutes. Return shrimp and eggs to wok with sliced scallions. Toss everything together and serve immediately.

title: French Onion Soup
description: Rich beef broth with caramelized onions, topped with toasted bread and melted cheese.
directions: Thinly slice onions. Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat. Add onions and cook for 35-40 minutes, stirring often, until deeply caramelized and golden brown. Add white wine and scrape up browned bits. Pour in beef broth and thyme, simmer for 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Toast bread slices. Ladle soup into oven-safe bowls, top each with toasted bread and grated gruyere. Broil for 2-3 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve immediately.

title: Veggie Frittata
description: Italian egg dish loaded with vegetables and cheese, baked until golden.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 degrees Celsius. Dice bell pepper, zucchini, and onion. Saute vegetables in an oven-safe skillet until softened. Whisk eggs with milk, salt, and pepper. Pour eggs over vegetables and cook for 2 minutes without stirring. Crumble feta on top. Transfer skillet to oven and bake for 15-18 minutes until eggs are set and top is golden. Let cool for 5 minutes, then slice into wedges. Serve warm or at room temperature with toast.

title: Chicken Parmesan
description: Breaded chicken cutlets topped with marinara sauce and melted mozzarella.
directions: Pound chicken breasts to even thickness. Set up breading station with flour, beaten eggs, and breadcrumbs mixed with parmesan. Coat each chicken piece in flour, then egg, then breadcrumbs. Pan-fry in oil for 4 minutes per side until golden. Transfer to a baking dish, top with marinara and mozzarella. Bake at 190 degrees Celsius for 15 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve over spaghetti with extra marinara and fresh basil.

title: Breakfast Burrito
description: Warm flour tortilla filled with scrambled eggs, cheese, beans, and salsa.
directions: Scramble eggs in a pan until just set. Warm tortillas in a dry skillet. Heat black beans. Lay tortillas flat and divide eggs, beans, shredded cheese, and salsa among them. Add sliced avocado. Fold in sides and roll up tightly. Optional: brown burritos in a skillet for 2 minutes per side until crispy. Serve with sour cream and extra salsa on the side.

title: Broccoli Cheddar Soup
description: Creamy soup with tender broccoli and sharp cheddar cheese.
directions: Chop broccoli into small florets. Melt butter in a large pot and saute diced onion until soft. Add flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually whisk in milk and chicken broth. Add broccoli and simmer for 15 minutes until tender. Use an immersion blender to partially puree soup, leaving some chunks. Stir in shredded cheddar until melted. Season with salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Serve hot with extra cheese and croutons.

title: Spaghetti Carbonara
description: Classic Roman pasta with crispy pancetta, eggs, and parmesan in a creamy sauce.
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water until al dente, reserve 1 cup pasta water. Dice pancetta and cook in a large skillet until crispy. Add minced garlic for 30 seconds. In a bowl, whisk eggs with grated parmesan and lots of black pepper. Drain pasta and add to skillet with pancetta. Remove from heat. Quickly toss in egg mixture, adding pasta water to create a creamy sauce. The heat from pasta cooks the eggs. Serve immediately with extra parmesan.

title: Quesadillas
description: Grilled flour tortillas filled with melted cheese and optional fillings.
directions: Dice bell pepper and onion, then saute until soft. Sprinkle shredded cheese on half of each tortilla. Add sauteed vegetables. Fold tortillas in half. Heat a large skillet over medium heat and cook quesadillas for 2-3 minutes per side until cheese is melted and tortilla is golden and crispy. Cut into wedges. Serve hot with sour cream, guacamole, and salsa for dipping.

title: Huevos Rancheros
description: Mexican breakfast with fried eggs on tortillas topped with salsa and beans.
directions: Warm refried or whole black beans. Heat tortillas in a dry skillet until soft and pliable. Fry eggs sunny-side up or to desired doneness. Place one tortilla on each plate and spread with beans. Top with a fried egg. Spoon warm salsa over eggs. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and add sliced avocado. Garnish with cilantro and serve with lime wedges.

title: Corn Chowder
description: Creamy soup with sweet corn, potatoes, and bacon.
directions: Cook bacon until crispy, crumble and set aside. In bacon fat, saute diced onion until soft. Add diced potatoes, corn, chicken broth, and thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Remove half the soup and puree until smooth, then return to pot. Stir in heavy cream and most of the bacon. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer for 5 more minutes. Serve hot topped with remaining bacon and fresh thyme.

title: Breakfast Hash
description: Skillet breakfast with crispy potatoes, eggs, peppers, and onions.
directions: Dice potatoes into small cubes. Heat oil in a large skillet and cook potatoes for 15 minutes until golden and crispy. Add diced onion and bell pepper, cook for 5 more minutes. Season with paprika, salt, and pepper. Make 4 wells in the hash and crack an egg into each. Cover and cook until eggs are set to your liking. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and let melt. Serve hot with hot sauce and toast.

title: Jalapeno Poppers
description: Spicy jalapenos stuffed with cream cheese and wrapped in bacon.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius. Halve jalapenos lengthwise and remove seeds. Mix cream cheese with shredded cheddar and garlic powder. Fill each jalapeno half with cheese mixture. Cut bacon strips in half and wrap around each popper. Secure with toothpicks. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 20-25 minutes until bacon is crispy. Remove toothpicks and serve hot with ranch dressing.

title: Mushroom Barley Soup
description: Hearty soup with earthy mushrooms and chewy barley in vegetable broth.
directions: Slice mushrooms and dice carrots, celery, and onion. Heat oil in a large pot and saute vegetables for 5 minutes. Add sliced mushrooms and cook until they release their liquid. Add barley, vegetable broth, and thyme. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes until barley is tender. Season with salt, pepper, and a splash of soy sauce for depth. Serve hot with crusty bread.

title: Molten Lava Cake
description: Individual chocolate cakes with gooey melted centers.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 degrees Celsius. Butter and flour four ramekins. Melt chocolate and butter together. Whisk eggs, egg yolks, and sugar until thick. Fold in chocolate mixture, then gently fold in flour. Divide batter among ramekins. Bake for 12 minutes until edges are firm but centers jiggle. Let stand for 1 minute. Invert onto plates and serve immediately with vanilla ice cream and berries.

title: Shakshuka
description: Middle Eastern dish with eggs poached in spicy tomato sauce with peppers and onions.
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet and saute diced onion and bell peppers until soft. Add minced garlic, cumin, and paprika, cook for 1 minute. Pour in crushed tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes until sauce thickens. Season with salt and pepper. Make 6 wells in the sauce and crack an egg into each. Cover and cook for 5-7 minutes until egg whites are set but yolks are still runny. Crumble feta on top and garnish with fresh parsley. Serve hot with crusty bread for dipping.

title: Lemon Herb Grilled Salmon
description: Succulent salmon fillets marinated in zesty lemon and herbs, then grilled to flaky perfection. A healthy and quick main course rich in omega-3s.
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the juice of one lemon, oil, dill, minced garlic, and salt. Place the salmon fillets in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over them, letting them sit for 15 minutes. Preheat your grill or grill pan to medium-high heat. Grill the salmon for about 4 to 5 minutes per side until cooked through and flaky. While the salmon rests, lightly grill the asparagus and lemon slices for garnish. Serve immediately.

title: Spicy Beef Tacos
description: Flavorful ground beef seasoned with cumin and chili, served in warm tortillas with fresh toppings. A crowd-pleasing meal that is easy to assemble.
directions: Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add the beef. Cook until browned, breaking it up with a spoon. Add the onion and cook until soft. Stir in the cumin, chili, paprika, and a pinch of salt. Pour in a splash of water and let it simmer until the liquid evaporates and the meat is coated in spices. Warm the tortillas in a dry pan. Assemble the tacos by filling tortillas with the meat mixture and topping with cilantro and a squeeze of lime.

title: Greek Quinoa Salad
description: A refreshing and protein-packed salad featuring fluffy quinoa, crisp vegetables, and salty feta cheese. Ideal for meal prep or a healthy side dish.
directions: Rinse the quinoa thoroughly. Place in a pot with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until water is absorbed. Fluff with a fork and let it cool. In a large bowl, combine the cooled quinoa, cucumber, tomato, and olives. Whisk together the oil and lemon juice, then pour over the salad. Toss gently to combine. Top with crumbled feta cheese before serving.

title: Ginger Chicken Stir Fry
description: Quickly cooked chicken and vegetables tossed in a savory ginger soy sauce.
directions: Cut the chicken into bite-sized pieces and vegetables into strips. Whisk soy sauce, minced ginger, minced garlic, sesame oil, and cornstarch in a small bowl. Heat a wok over high heat and cook the chicken until browned. Add the vegetables and stir-fry for 3 minutes until crisp-tender. Pour the sauce over the mixture and cook until thickened. Serve immediately over cooked rice.

title: Teriyaki Chicken Bowl
description: Tender chicken thighs glazed in a glossy homemade sweet and savory sauce. Served over rice for a satisfying meal.
directions: Cut the chicken into bite-sized pieces. In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, sugar, mirin, minced ginger, minced garlic, and cornstarch. Heat the oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook until browned and cooked through. Pour the sauce mixture over the chicken and stir constantly. Cook for another 2 to 3 minutes until the sauce thickens and coats the meat. Serve immediately.

title: Spinach Mushroom Frittata
description: An egg-based Italian dish similar to an omelet but finished in the oven. Great for using up leftover vegetables.
directions: Preheat your oven to 180 degrees Celsius. Whisk the eggs, milk, and salt in a bowl. Heat the olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Saute the chopped onion and sliced mushrooms until browned. Add the spinach and cook until wilted. Pour the egg mixture over the vegetables and sprinkle with cheese. Cook on the stovetop for 2 minutes until the edges set, then transfer the skillet to the oven. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the center is set.

title: Beef and Broccoli
description: A popular Chinese takeout dish that you can easily make at home. The beef is tender and the sauce is savory.
directions: Slice the beef thinly against the grain and cut broccoli into florets. Whisk soy sauce, brown sugar, sesame oil, minced ginger, and minced garlic in a bowl. Heat half the oil in a wok and stir-fry the broccoli for 3 minutes, then remove. Heat the remaining oil and sear the beef until browned. Return the broccoli to the pan and pour in the sauce. Toss everything together and cook for 2 minutes until hot and coated.

title: Chicken Quesadillas
description: Crispy tortillas filled with melted cheese and seasoned chicken. A quick and crowd-pleasing meal.
directions: Dice the cooked chicken, bell pepper, and onion. Toss the chicken with cumin. Heat a little butter in a skillet over medium heat. Place one tortilla in the pan. Sprinkle cheese over the whole tortilla, then scatter chicken and vegetables over one half. Fold the tortilla over to create a half-moon shape. Cook for 3 minutes per side until the tortilla is golden crispy and the cheese is melted. Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: Greek Yogurt Bowl
description: A refreshing and healthy start to the day packed with probiotics and fresh fruit.
directions: Spoon the yogurt into a serving bowl. Wash and slice the strawberries. Arrange the strawberries, blueberries, and granola on top of the yogurt. Drizzle generously with honey just before eating.

title: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: A rich and tangy mushroom pasta dish inspired by the Russian classic but without the beef.
directions: Boil the noodles according to package directions. In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add chopped onion and cook until soft. Add sliced mushrooms and thyme, cooking until the liquid evaporates and mushrooms are browned. Sprinkle flour over the vegetables and stir for 1 minute. Slowly whisk in the broth and simmer until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in the sour cream. Toss with the cooked noodles and serve.

title: Chicken Fajitas
description: Sizzling strips of chicken and peppers served with warm tortillas.
directions: Slice the chicken, peppers, and onion into strips. In a bowl, toss the chicken with chili powder, cumin, lime juice, and half the oil. Heat the remaining oil in a large cast-iron skillet over high heat. Add the chicken and cook until seared and cooked through, then remove. Add the peppers and onions to the same pan, scraping up any browned bits, and cook until charred but crisp. Return chicken to the pan to mix. Serve immediately with warmed tortillas.

title: Lentil Bolognese
description: A hearty plant-based version of the meat sauce, excellent served over spaghetti.
directions: Finely dice the onion, carrot, and celery. Saute vegetables in olive oil in a large pot until soft. Add the dried lentils, tomato sauce, vegetable broth, and oregano. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 35 to 40 minutes until lentils are tender and sauce is thick. While the sauce simmers, cook spaghetti in salted water. Toss the drained pasta with the sauce and serve.

title: Beef and Broccoli
description: A takeout favorite you can make at home with tender beef slices and crisp broccoli florets.
directions: Slice beef thinly against the grain. Whisk soy sauce, minced ginger, minced garlic, brown sugar, sesame oil, and cornstarch in a bowl. Blanch broccoli florets in boiling water for 2 minutes, then drain. Heat a wok over high heat with a little oil. Sear the beef slices for 2 minutes. Add the sauce and cook until it bubbles and thickens slightly. Toss in the broccoli to coat. Serve over rice.

title: Classic French Toast
description: Slices of bread soaked in a spiced egg custard and pan-fried.
directions: Whisk eggs, milk, cinnamon, and vanilla in a shallow dish. Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat. Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, allowing it to soak for a few seconds on each side. Place in the skillet and cook for 3 to 4 minutes per side until golden brown. Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: Spaghetti Carbonara
description: A classic Roman pasta dish made with eggs, hard cheese, cured pork, and black pepper. It is creamy without the use of cream.
directions: Boil the spaghetti in salted water. While pasta cooks, fry the pancetta in a large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Add the whole garlic cloves to flavor the fat, then remove them. In a bowl, whisk the eggs, parmesan, and pepper. Drain the pasta, reserving some water. Toss the hot pasta into the skillet with the pancetta. Remove from heat and quickly mix in the egg mixture, adding pasta water to create a creamy sauce. Serve immediately.

title: Chicken Quesadilla
description: Crispy tortillas filled with melted cheese and seasoned chicken. A quick and satisfying meal.
directions: Shred the cooked chicken. Heat a skillet over medium heat and melt a little butter. Place a tortilla in the pan. Sprinkle half the cheese and half the chicken over the tortilla. Top with another tortilla. Cook for 3 minutes until the bottom is golden and cheese is melting. Flip carefully and cook the other side for 2 minutes. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Cut into wedges and serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: Vegetable Fried Rice
description: A great way to use leftover rice, tossed with colorful vegetables and savory soy sauce.
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large pan. Scramble the eggs and remove them. Add the diced carrots and peas to the pan, stir-frying for 3 minutes. Add the cooked cold rice, breaking up any clumps. Stir in the soy sauce and cook until the rice is hot and coated. Mix the eggs back in along with chopped scallions. Serve hot.

title: Tomato Bruschetta
description: Grilled bread topped with a fresh mixture of tomatoes, basil, and garlic. A popular starter.
directions: Slice the baguette and toast the slices in the oven or on a grill until crisp. Rub a clove of raw garlic over the hot bread. Dice the tomatoes and chop the basil. In a bowl, combine tomatoes, basil, minced garlic, olive oil, vinegar, and salt. Spoon the mixture onto the toasted bread slices and serve immediately.

title: Beef Shish Kabob
description: Skewered beef and vegetables marinated and grilled to perfection.
directions: Cut the beef, peppers, and onion into 1-inch chunks. Whisk soy sauce, oil, and minced garlic in a bowl. Marinate the beef in the mixture for at least 30 minutes. Thread beef, peppers, onion, and whole mushrooms onto skewers alternating ingredients. Preheat grill to medium-high. Grill skewers for 10 minutes, turning occasionally, until beef is cooked to your liking.

title: Traditional Shepherds Pie
description: Savory ground meat and vegetables topped with a crust of creamy mashed potatoes.
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then mash with butter and milk. In a skillet, cook beef and onion until browned. Stir in diced carrots and peas, cooking for 5 minutes. Add broth and simmer briefly. Transfer meat mixture to a baking dish and spread mashed potatoes on top. Bake at 200 degrees Celsius for 25 minutes until golden.

title: Classic Chicken Noodle Soup
description: The ultimate comfort food for a cold day or when you are feeling under the weather.
directions: Saute chopped onion, carrot, and celery in a large pot until soft. Add the chicken breast and broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 minutes until chicken is cooked. Remove chicken, shred it, and return to pot. Add noodles and thyme, cooking for another 8 minutes until noodles are tender.

title: Shakshuka
description: Eggs poached in a spicy tomato and pepper sauce. Great with crusty bread.
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until soft. Add garlic and spices, cooking for a minute. Add chopped tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes until sauce thickens. Make four small wells in the sauce and crack an egg into each. Cover pan and cook for 5 to 7 minutes until egg whites are set but yolks are runny.

title: Fresh Gazpacho
description: A chilled vegetable soup originating from Spain. Refreshing on a hot summer day.
directions: Roughly chop all vegetables. Place them in a blender with vinegar, olive oil, and a pinch of salt. Blend until smooth. Strain if a finer texture is desired. Chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: Traditional Ratatouille
description: A vegetable stew from Provence featuring eggplant, zucchini, and peppers.
directions: Dice all vegetables into equal sizes. Heat oil in a large pot. Saute onion and garlic until soft. Add eggplant and peppers, cooking for 5 minutes. Add zucchini and tomatoes. Season with thyme and salt. Cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes until vegetables are tender but not mushy.

title: Chicken Satay
description: Grilled skewers of marinated chicken served with a rich peanut sauce.
directions: Cut chicken into strips and thread onto skewers. Whisk peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, sugar, minced garlic, and coconut milk in a bowl. Brush some sauce over the chicken. Grill skewers for 4 to 5 minutes per side until cooked. Serve with the remaining sauce for dipping.

title: Egg Salad
description: Chopped hard-boiled eggs mixed with mayonnaise and mustard. Classic filling for sandwiches.
directions: Place eggs in a pot of water, boil, remove from heat and let sit for 10 minutes. Cool eggs in ice water and peel. Chop the eggs into small pieces. In a bowl, mix eggs with mayonnaise, mustard, chopped chives, salt, and pepper. Stir gently until combined. Serve on bread or lettuce.

title: Spinach Frittata
description: An Italian egg-based dish similar to an omelet or crustless quiche, enriched with potatoes and greens.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius. Peel and slice the potato thinly. Heat oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Cook potato and onion until tender. Add spinach and cook until wilted. Whisk eggs, milk, and cheese in a bowl. Pour mixture over the vegetables. Cook for 2 minutes on stovetop until edges set, then transfer to oven. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until puffy and golden.

title: Classic French Onion Soup
description: Rich beef broth packed with caramelized onions and topped with cheesy toasted bread.
directions: Slice onions thinly. Melt butter in a large pot and cook onions over medium-low heat for 30 minutes until deep brown and caramelized. Add wine to deglaze the pan. Add broth and thyme, simmering for 20 minutes. Slice baguette and toast. Ladle soup into oven-safe bowls, top with bread and grated cheese. Broil in oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: Hollowed peppers filled with a savory mixture of meat, rice, and tomato sauce.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 degrees Celsius. Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds. Cook rice. Brown beef with onion and garlic in a skillet. Mix cooked beef, rice, and half the tomato sauce. Stuff peppers with the mixture and place in a baking dish. Top with remaining sauce and cheese. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until peppers are tender.

title: Spicy Mango Quinoa Salad
description: A refreshing and vibrant salad featuring sweet mango, spicy jalapeno, and fluffy quinoa. It serves as a light lunch or a colorful side dish.
directions: Rinse the quinoa under cold water. Combine quinoa and water in a pot, bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes until water is absorbed. Fluff with a fork and let cool completely. Peel the mango and dice the flesh into small cubes. Remove seeds from the jalapeno and mince finely. Chop the cilantro. In a large bowl, whisk together the juice of the lime, olive oil, and salt. Add the cooled quinoa, mango, jalapeno, and cilantro to the bowl and toss to coat evenly. Chill for 30 minutes before serving to allow flavors to meld.

title: Sweet Potato Black Bean Enchiladas
description: Hearty vegetarian enchiladas filled with spiced sweet potatoes and black beans. Baked in a zesty red sauce and topped with melted cheese.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 degrees Celsius. Peel and dice the sweet potatoes into small cubes. Boil or steam sweet potatoes until tender, about 10 minutes. Dice the onion. In a bowl, mash the cooked sweet potatoes slightly and mix with rinsed black beans, diced onion, cumin, chili powder, and half cup of cheese. Pour a thin layer of enchilada sauce into a baking dish. Spoon the filling into each tortilla, roll them up, and place seam-side down in the dish. Pour the remaining sauce over the rolls and top with the remaining cheese. Bake for 20 minutes until the cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.

title: Coconut Curry Lentil Soup
description: A warming and creamy soup packed with protein-rich lentils and spinach. The broth is flavored with aromatic curry spices and coconut milk.
directions: Dice the onion and mince the garlic and ginger. Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat. Saute the onion until translucent, then add garlic, ginger, and curry powder, stirring for 1 minute until fragrant. Add the lentils and vegetable broth to the pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20-25 minutes until lentils are tender. Stir in the coconut milk and simmer for another 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the spinach until wilted. Season with salt to taste before serving.

title: Mediterranean Chickpea Stew
description: A robust and healthy stew featuring chickpeas simmered in a spiced tomato sauce with spinach. Perfect for a comforting meatless meal.
directions: Dice the onion and mince the garlic. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Saute onion until soft, about 5 minutes, then add garlic, cumin, and paprika, cooking for another minute. Add the canned tomatoes (with juices) and rinsed chickpeas. Bring to a boil, break up the tomatoes with a spoon, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 minutes to thicken. Stir in the spinach and cook for 2-3 minutes until wilted. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot with crusty bread.

title: Creamy Mushroom Risotto
description: Rich and comforting rice dish cooked slowly with white wine and parmesan.
directions: Warm the broth in a separate saucepan. Dice the onion and slice the mushrooms. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a large pot over medium heat. Saute the onions and mushrooms until soft. Add the arborio rice and toast for 1 minute. Pour in the white wine and stir until absorbed. Gradually add warm broth one ladle at a time, stirring constantly and waiting for liquid to absorb before adding more. Continue this process for about 20 minutes until rice is creamy and tender. Remove from heat and stir in the remaining butter and parmesan cheese.

title: Baked Lemon Salmon
description: A healthy one-pan dinner featuring flaky fish and tender asparagus.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius. Trim the woody ends off the asparagus. Place salmon fillets and asparagus on a baking sheet lined with foil. Drizzle olive oil over the asparagus and season with salt. Mince the garlic and mix with melted butter and dill. Brush the salmon generously with the garlic butter mixture. Slice the lemon and place rounds on top of the salmon. Bake for 12-15 minutes until the salmon is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.

title: Teriyaki Tofu Bowl
description: Crispy tofu cubes served with steamed rice and a sweet glaze.
directions: Press the tofu to remove excess water, then cut into cubes. Toss tofu cubes in cornstarch. Cook the rice according to package instructions. In a small pan, simmer soy sauce, mirin, brown sugar, and grated ginger until slightly thickened. Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Pan-fry the tofu cubes until golden and crispy on all sides. Pour the teriyaki sauce over the tofu in the pan and toss to coat. Serve the sticky tofu over a bed of steamed rice.

title: Classic Spaghetti Carbonara
description: A traditional Roman pasta dish made with eggs, cheese, and cured pork. Creamy and savory without using any actual cream.
directions: Boil a large pot of salted water and cook spaghetti until al dente. While pasta cooks, chop the bacon and mince the garlic. Fry the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crisp, then add garlic and cook for 1 minute. In a bowl, whisk eggs, parmesan, and black pepper together. Reserve 1 cup of pasta water, then drain the spaghetti. Add hot pasta to the skillet with bacon and toss to coat with fat. Remove pan from heat completely. Pour in the egg mixture while tossing the pasta vigorously to create a creamy sauce without scrambling the eggs. Add reserved pasta water if needed for consistency.

title: Sesame Ginger Tofu
description: Crispy tofu cubes coated in a sticky and sweet ginger sesame sauce. Served with steamed broccoli for a complete meal.
directions: Press tofu to remove water and cut into cubes. Toss tofu in cornstarch. Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and pan-fry tofu until golden. Remove tofu. Steam broccoli florets until tender. In the same skillet, whisk soy sauce, maple syrup, sesame oil, minced ginger, and minced garlic. Simmer sauce for 2 minutes until it bubbles and thickens slightly. Return tofu and broccoli to the pan and toss to coat evenly in the glaze.

title: Berry Yogurt Breakfast Bowl
description: A quick and healthy breakfast bowl loaded with antioxidants and crunch.
directions: Wash the berries and slice the strawberries. Scoop the yogurt into a serving bowl. Top evenly with granola, blueberries, and strawberry slices. Drizzle honey over the top just before eating.

title: Red Lentil Lemon Soup
description: A smooth and warming soup with a bright citrus finish. The lentils break down to create a naturally creamy texture.
directions: Dice the onion and carrot. Rinse the lentils. Heat olive oil in a pot over medium heat and saute onion and carrot for 5 minutes. Stir in cumin and turmeric. Add lentils and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 minutes until lentils are completely soft. Puree the soup with an immersion blender or standard blender until smooth. Stir in the juice of one lemon and season with salt before serving.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp Pasta
description: Tender shrimp tossed with linguine in a rich and garlicky butter sauce. Finished with fresh parsley and lemon for zest.
directions: Boil the linguine in salted water according to package directions. While pasta cooks, melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant. Add the shrimp and cook for 3 to 4 minutes until pink and opaque. Squeeze the juice of the lemon into the pan. Toss the drained pasta with the shrimp and sauce. Garnish with chopped parsley and parmesan cheese before serving.

title: Vegetarian Bean Chili
description: A hearty and spicy stew packed with two types of beans and corn. Perfect for a cold evening.
directions: Dice the onion and bell pepper. Rinse both types of beans. Heat a splash of water or oil in a large pot and saute the onion and pepper until soft. Stir in the chili powder and cumin. Add the crushed tomatoes, kidney beans, black beans, and corn. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes. Season with salt to taste.

title: Chicken Quesadillas
description: Crispy tortillas filled with seasoned chicken and melted cheese. Served with salsa for dipping.
directions: Dice the chicken, onion, and bell pepper. Cook the chicken in a skillet over medium heat until cooked through, then remove. Saute the onion and pepper until soft. Melt a little butter in the skillet. Place a tortilla in the pan, top with cheese, chicken, and veggies, then fold in half. Cook until golden brown on both sides and cheese is melted. Repeat with remaining tortillas.

title: Greek Yogurt Parfait
description: Layers of creamy yogurt, sweet honey, and crunchy granola. A simple no-cook breakfast.
directions: Wash the fruit. Place half the yogurt in a glass. Top with half the granola and berries. Repeat the layers with remaining yogurt, granola, and fruit. Drizzle generously with honey.

title: Creamy Tomato Basil Soup
description: Smooth and velvety soup made from ripe tomatoes and fresh herbs.
directions: Dice the onion and mince the garlic. Melt butter in a pot over medium heat. Saute onion and garlic until soft. Add canned tomatoes and broth. Simmer for 20 minutes. Blend the soup until smooth using a blender. Stir in heavy cream and chopped fresh basil. Season with salt and pepper.

title: Coconut Cauliflower Curry
description: Mild and creamy vegan curry loaded with vegetables.
directions: Cut cauliflower into florets and dice the onion. Heat oil in a large pot and saute the onion until translucent. Stir in curry powder. Add cauliflower, drained chickpeas, and coconut milk. Simmer covered for 15 minutes until cauliflower is tender. Stir in the peas and cook for 2 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: Vegetable Minestrone Soup
description: Classic Italian soup with vegetables, beans, and pasta in a tomato broth.
directions: Dice carrots and celery. In a large pot, combine broth, tomatoes, carrots, and celery. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Add the pasta and kidney beans, cooking for another 10 minutes until pasta is tender. Stir in the spinach and cook for 2 minutes until wilted. Season with salt and pepper.

title: Gourmet Grilled Cheese
description: An elevated version of the classic sandwich with caramelized onions.
directions: Slice the onion thinly. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of butter over low heat for 15 minutes until caramelized, adding vinegar at the end. Butter one side of each bread slice. Layer cheddar, gruyere, and onions between the unbuttered sides of the bread. Grill in a pan over medium heat until golden brown and cheese melts.

title: Homemade Falafel Wrap
description: Crispy chickpea balls served in a wrap with tahini and veggies.
directions: Blend drained chickpeas, parsley, garlic, cumin, and flour in a food processor until coarse. Form into small patties. Heat oil in a skillet and fry falafel patties until brown and crispy, about 3 minutes per side. Warm the tortillas. Assemble wraps with falafel, tahini, and any fresh veggies desired.

title: Lemon Dill Salmon Cakes
description: Flaky salmon patties mixed with breadcrumbs and herbs, pan-fried to perfection.
directions: Drain the salmon and remove any skin or bones. In a bowl, mix salmon, breadcrumbs, beaten eggs, chopped dill, mayonnaise, and lemon juice. Form mixture into patties. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Cook patties for 4 minutes on each side until golden brown and crispy.

title: Spinach Mushroom Frittata
description: A fluffy baked egg dish loaded with sauteed vegetables and cheese.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 degrees Celsius. Whisk eggs, milk, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Slice the mushrooms and onion. Melt butter in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Saute onion and mushrooms for 5 minutes, then add spinach until wilted. Pour the egg mixture over the vegetables and sprinkle with cheese. Cook on stovetop for 2 minutes until edges set, then transfer to the oven. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until eggs are set.

title: Mediterranean Quinoa Salad
description: A light and healthy grain salad packed with Greek flavors.
directions: Cook quinoa in water according to package directions, then cool. Dice the cucumber and tomatoes. Pit and slice the olives. In a large bowl, combine cooled quinoa, vegetables, olives, and crumbled feta. Dress with olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Toss well.

title: Lemon Garlic Shrimp Skewers
description: Grilled shrimp marinated in zesty lemon and herbs.
directions: Soak wooden skewers in water. In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, minced garlic, chopped parsley, and paprika. Toss shrimp in the marinade and let sit for 15 minutes. Thread shrimp onto skewers. Heat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat. Cook skewers for 2 to 3 minutes per side until shrimp are pink and slightly charred.

title: Peanut Chicken Satay
description: Tender chicken strips served with a rich and creamy peanut dipping sauce.
directions: Cut chicken into strips and season with curry powder. Saute chicken in a pan with a little oil until cooked through. In a small saucepan, combine peanut butter, coconut milk, soy sauce, lime juice, and sugar. Whisk over low heat until smooth and warm. Serve chicken with the sauce.

title: Homestyle Chicken Noodle Soup
description: Comforting broth with chicken, veggies, and egg noodles.
directions: Dice onion, carrots, and celery. Put chicken breast, broth, and vegetables in a pot. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 minutes until chicken is cooked. Remove chicken, shred it, and return to pot. Add thyme and dry noodles. Simmer for another 8 minutes until noodles are soft.

title: Baked Sweet Potato Fries
description: Healthy alternative to french fries, baked until crisp and seasoned with paprika.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 degrees Celsius. Cut sweet potatoes into sticks. Toss them in a bag with cornstarch to coat lightly. Remove from bag and toss with oil, paprika, garlic powder, and salt. Spread in a single layer on a baking sheet, ensuring they do not touch. Bake for 15 minutes, flip, and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until crispy.

title: Chicken Cobb Salad
description: A composed salad featuring rows of chicken, bacon, eggs, and cheese.
directions: Cook the chicken and bacon; hard boil the eggs. Chop lettuce, chicken, bacon, eggs, avocado, and tomatoes. Arrange lettuce on a large platter. Place the ingredients in rows over the lettuce. Sprinkle blue cheese over the top. Serve with your favorite dressing.

title: Classic Shakshuka
description: Poached eggs simmered in a spiced tomato and pepper sauce.
directions: Dice the onion and bell pepper. Heat oil in a deep skillet and saute veggies until soft. Add minced garlic, cumin, and paprika, cooking for 1 minute. Pour in crushed tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes to thicken. Make four wells in the sauce and crack an egg into each. Cover and cook on low for 8 minutes until whites set. Sprinkle with feta cheese.

title: Crispy Zucchini Fritters
description: Golden brown patties made from shredded zucchini. A great way to eat more vegetables.
directions: Grate the zucchini and squeeze out as much moisture as possible using a towel. In a bowl, mix zucchini, flour, parmesan, beaten egg, minced garlic, chopped scallions, salt, and pepper. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Drop spoonfuls of batter into the pan and flatten slightly. Fry for 3 minutes per side until crispy and browned.

title: Honey Mustard Chicken
description: Baked chicken breast smothered in a tangy and sweet sauce.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius. In a small bowl, whisk together honey, mustard, mayonnaise, lemon juice, and paprika. Place chicken breasts in a baking dish and season with salt. Pour the sauce over the chicken. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce is bubbly.

title: Mushroom Barley Soup
description: Nutty barley and earthy mushrooms simmered in a flavorful broth.
directions: Dice onion, carrots, and celery; slice the mushrooms. Saute vegetables in a large pot until soft. Add mushrooms and cook until browned. Stir in rinsed barley, vegetable broth, and thyme. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 45 minutes until barley is tender. Season with salt and pepper.

title: Greek Tzatziki Dip
description: Cool and refreshing yogurt dip flavored with cucumber and garlic.
directions: Grate the cucumber and squeeze out excess water firmly using a towel. In a bowl, combine the drained cucumber with greek yogurt. Stir in minced garlic, chopped fresh dill, lemon juice, olive oil, and salt. Chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes to let flavors meld before serving.

title: Herb Lemon Chicken
description: A bright and aromatic chicken dish infused with citrus and simple herbs. Perfect for a light yet satisfying dinner.
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, basil, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Mix until smooth. Coat the chicken thoroughly and rest for 20 minutes. Heat a pan on medium and place the chicken inside. Cook each side until browned, then lower the heat and cover for a few minutes until fully done. Let it rest briefly before serving.

title: Tomato Basil Pasta
description: An Italian-style pasta featuring vibrant tomato and basil flavors. Quick to prepare and comforting for any meal.
directions: Boil noodles until tender and drain. Heat oil in a pan and add crushed tomato and garlic. Cook until the tomato softens into a sauce. Add salt and pepper, then simmer for a few minutes. Stir in the noodles and mix well. Remove from heat and fold in basil before serving.

title: Lentil Tomato Soup
description: A warm and filling soup made with hearty lentils and tomatoes. Perfect for a wholesome dinner.
directions: Place lentils, chopped tomato, onion, garlic, salt, and pepper into a pot. Add water and bring to a boil. Lower the heat and simmer until the lentils become soft. Stir occasionally. When done, blend lightly for a smoother texture or keep chunky. Serve hot.

title: Honey Orange Salmon
description: A sweet and citrus-glazed salmon that caramelizes beautifully as it bakes. Perfect for a fresh dinner.
directions: Mix honey with orange juice, salt, pepper, and oil. Place salmon on a tray and brush with the mixture. Bake at medium heat for about 15-20 minutes, basting halfway through. Remove when the salmon flakes easily with a fork.

title: Chickpea Spinach Stew
description: A nourishing stew combining chickpeas and spinach for a balanced, plant-based dinner. Warm and satisfying.
directions: Heat oil in a pot and cook onion until soft. Add tomato and stir until it breaks down. Add chickpeas with a small amount of water and simmer. Stir in spinach, salt, and pepper. Cook until all ingredients are tender and the stew thickens slightly.

title: Beef Rice Skillet
description: A hearty skillet meal combining seasoned beef and rice. Simple and filling for busy days.
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and cook beef and onion until browned. Add rice and stir for a minute. Pour in water, add salt and pepper, then cover and simmer until the rice absorbs the liquid. Fluff before serving.

title: Mint Lemon Salad
description: A crisp and refreshing salad with bright lemon and cool mint. Great as a side or light lunch.
directions: Place lettuce and mint in a bowl. Mix lemon juice, oil, salt, and pepper in a small container. Pour the mixture over the salad and toss gently until coated.

title: Olive Herb Chicken
description: A simple herb-infused chicken with a subtle olive flavor.
directions: Mix olive oil, lemon juice, crushed garlic, basil, salt, and black pepper in a bowl. Coat the chicken breast on all sides and let it rest for 20 minutes. Heat a pan to medium and cook the chicken until each side browns. Lower the heat and cover the pan to finish cooking. Rest for a few minutes before slicing.

title: Spicy Tomato Noodles
description: A vibrant noodle dish with a spicy tomato base and light seasoning.
directions: Boil the noodles until soft, then drain. Heat olive oil in a pan and add chopped red onion and tomato. Cook until the tomato turns into a sauce, then add chili, salt, and black pepper. Add the noodles, stir well, and simmer briefly to blend the flavors.

title: Ginger Rice Bowl
description: A warm rice bowl with gentle ginger notes.
directions: Cook the rice separately. Heat oil in a pan and add sliced ginger and tofu. Stir for several minutes until lightly browned. Add soy sauce and cook briefly until absorbed. Serve the mixture on top of the rice and garnish with green onion.

title: Creamy Lentil Soup
description: A smooth lentil soup with mild seasoning for a warm and filling meal.
directions: Combine lentils, chopped carrot, onion, garlic, water, salt, and cumin in a pot. Boil and then simmer until the lentils soften. Mash lightly or blend for a creamier texture. Simmer for a few minutes more and serve warm.

title: Orange Soy Salmon
description: A salmon dish glazed with a sweet citrus soy mixture.
directions: Whisk orange juice, soy sauce, honey, black pepper, and oil. Place salmon on a tray and pour the mixture over it. Bake at medium heat for 15-20 minutes, brushing with the sauce halfway through.

title: Chickpea Pepper Stew
description: A hearty stew with chickpeas and peppers for a balanced meal.
directions: Heat oil in a pot and add chopped onion and red pepper. Cook until softened. Add tomato and stir until it forms a base. Add chickpeas with water to cover and simmer until thick. Season with salt and black pepper.

title: Beef Tomato Skillet
description: Ground beef cooked in a tomato base makes a quick and filling meal.
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil. Add chopped tomato and cook until it creates a sauce. Add rice and stir briefly. Pour in water to cover the rice and simmer until the liquid is absorbed and rice softens.

title: Mint Lemon Couscous
description: A fresh couscous dish with mint and lemon for a bright flavor.
directions: Pour hot water over couscous in a bowl and cover for a few minutes. Fluff with a fork. Add mint, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and black pepper. Mix gently and serve.

title: Chicken Rice Bowl
description: A simple rice bowl with seasoned chicken and vegetables.
directions: Cook rice in water until soft. Heat olive oil in a pan and add chopped onion and carrot. Cook for several minutes, then add sliced chicken breast. Pour soy sauce over the mixture and cook until the chicken is fully done. Serve everything over warm rice.

title: Lemon Garlic Shrimp
description: Shrimp cooked in lemon and garlic for a bright and savory dish.
directions: Melt butter in a pan and add minced garlic. Cook for one minute, then add shrimp. Squeeze lemon juice over the shrimp and add salt and black pepper. Cook until the shrimp turn pink, then mix in chopped parsley and serve immediately.

title: Veggie Egg Skillet
description: A hearty vegetable and egg mix perfect for breakfast.
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet and add chopped onion and tomato. Cook until the vegetables soften, then add spinach and wait for it to wilt. Crack eggs on top, cover the skillet, and cook on low heat until the eggs reach the desired firmness. Season with salt and serve.

title: Chickpea Salad Bowl
description: A protein rich bowl with chickpeas and crisp vegetables.
directions: Rinse chickpeas and place them in a bowl. Add chopped cucumber, tomato, and parsley. Mix olive oil with squeezed lemon juice and salt, then pour over the salad. Toss everything well and let it sit for several minutes before serving.

title: Beef Noodle Stir
description: A quick stir dish with beef, noodles, and light seasoning.
directions: Boil noodles until soft. Heat oil in a pan and add garlic and onion. Cook until fragrant, then add ground beef and stir until browned. Add carrot slices and soy sauce, then mix in the cooked noodles. Stir everything for a few minutes and serve hot.

title: Potato Carrot Soup
description: A warm and creamy vegetable soup.
directions: Heat olive oil in a pot and add chopped onion and garlic. Add diced potato and carrot, then pour water to cover. Cook on medium heat until the vegetables soften. Blend the soup until smooth, season with salt and black pepper, then simmer for 5 more minutes before serving.

title: Garlic Butter Rice
description: A simple side dish with buttery garlic flavor.
directions: Melt butter in a pot and add minced garlic. Cook briefly, then add rice and stir to coat. Pour in water according to the rice ratio and add salt. Cook on low heat until the rice absorbs all liquid. Fluff with a fork and add black pepper before serving.

title: Mushroom Egg Toast
description: A quick toast with mushroom and egg.
directions: Heat butter in a pan and cook sliced mushroom until browned. Toast the bread and fry the egg in the same pan. Place the mushroom on the bread, top with the egg, and season with salt and black pepper before serving.

title: Simple Tuna Pasta
description: A light pasta dish combined with tuna and herbs.
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until soft. Drain and mix in olive oil. Add tuna and chopped parsley. Squeeze lemon juice over the mixture, season with salt, combine everything well, and serve warm.

title: Tuna Potato Mix
description: A simple warm bowl combining tuna and potato.
directions: Boil potatoes until soft, then cut into chunks. Add tuna, olive oil, chopped parsley, salt, and squeezed lemon juice. Mix carefully and serve warm.

title: Egg Rice Stir
description: A quick stir fry with rice and egg.
directions: Cook rice and set aside. Heat olive oil and cook chopped onion and carrot. Push vegetables aside, scramble eggs in the same pan, then add rice and soy sauce. Stir on high heat for 3 minutes and serve.

title: Spinach Lentil Soup
description: A hearty lentil soup with spinach.
directions: Cook lentils in water until soft. In another pan cook chopped onion and tomato in olive oil, then add spinach and cook briefly. Combine with lentils, season with salt, simmer 10 minutes and serve.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp
description: Shrimp cooked in garlic butter with herbs.
directions: Melt butter and cook minced garlic for 1 minute. Add shrimp and cook until pink. Add parsley, salt, and black pepper. Stir for 1 more minute and serve hot.

title: Beef Tomato Skillet
description: A quick skillet dish combining beef and tomato.
directions: Heat olive oil, cook chopped onion and garlic, then add ground beef and brown it. Add chopped tomato and cook until softened. Season with salt and serve with rice or bread.

title: Chili Bean Rice
description: A spicy bean mix served over rice.
directions: Cook rice separately. Heat olive oil, cook chopped onion, add beans and chili powder. Add salt and cook 5 minutes. Serve mixture over rice.

title: Carrot Pepper Salad
description: A crunchy salad with simple seasoning.
directions: Grate carrot and slice red pepper. Add chopped parsley. Mix olive oil, lemon juice, and salt. Combine everything and serve.

title: Tomato Egg Bowl
description: A warm and quick egg bowl with tomato.
directions: Cook chopped tomato in olive oil until soft. Beat eggs with salt and black pepper, pour them over the tomato, and cook on low heat until set. Serve warm.

title: Lemon Herb Rice
description: A citrus flavored rice with herbs.
directions: Cook rice with water and salt. When done, mix in olive oil, parsley, and squeezed lemon juice. Stir and serve.

title: Simple Chicken Soup
description: A warm broth with chicken and vegetables.
directions: Boil chicken breast in water until cooked. Add chopped carrot and onion, simmer until soft. Add salt, black pepper, and parsley. Serve hot.

title: Tofu Rice Plate
description: A simple rice plate topped with tofu.
directions: Cook rice separately. Fry tofu in olive oil until golden. Add chopped onion and soy sauce. Place mixture over rice and serve.

title: Zucchini Pasta Bowl
description: Pasta combined with zucchini in a light sauce.
directions: Cook pasta. In a pan cook sliced zucchini and garlic in olive oil. Add pasta, salt, and black pepper. Mix and heat for 1 minute before serving.

title: Chickpea Curry
description: A mild chickpea curry dish.
directions: Cook onion in olive oil, add tomato and curry powder. Add chickpeas and water. Simmer 15 minutes and season with salt.

title: Pea Carrot Stew
description: A simple vegetable stew.
directions: Cook onion in olive oil, add peas, carrot, and potato. Add water and salt. Simmer until vegetables soften.

title: Eggplant Tomato Bake
description: A baked mix of eggplant and tomato.
directions: Slice eggplant and tomato. Mix with olive oil, salt, and black pepper. Bake at 190C for 25 minutes and serve warm.

title: Garlic Spinach Rice
description: Rice mixed with garlic and spinach.
directions: Cook rice. In a pan cook garlic and spinach in olive oil. Mix with rice, add salt, stir and serve.

title: Yogurt Cucumber Salad
description: A refreshing yogurt based salad.
directions: Mix yogurt with minced garlic and salt. Add chopped cucumber and stir. Drizzle olive oil on top and serve cold.

title: Lemon Herb Chicken
description: A bright and simple chicken dish with citrus notes.
directions: Mix lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, basil, and black pepper in a bowl. Coat chicken breast and rest 20 minutes. Heat a pan on medium and cook chicken for 6 to 7 minutes each side until golden. Serve warm.

title: Tomato Rice Bowl
description: A simple rice bowl with tomato flavor and mild seasoning.
directions: Cook rice in water until soft. Heat olive oil in a pot and add onion and tomato. Stir for 5 minutes then add salt and black pepper. Mix in cooked rice and simmer 3 minutes before serving.

title: Coconut Bean Curry
description: A creamy bean curry with coconut flavor.
directions: Heat a pan and cook onion and garlic in oil for 4 minutes. Add curry powder and stir. Pour in coconut milk and simmer 5 minutes. Add beans and cook 10 minutes on low heat. Adjust seasoning and serve.

title: Garlic Butter Pasta
description: A simple pasta coated in garlic butter sauce.
directions: Boil pasta until tender. Melt butter in a pan and add garlic. Cook for 2 minutes. Mix pasta into butter and stir in parmesan, salt, and black pepper. Serve hot.

title: Honey Soy Chicken
description: A sweet and savory chicken dish with a glossy sauce.
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, garlic, and ginger. Coat chicken and rest 20 minutes. Heat oil in a pan, cook chicken 7 minutes per side. Reduce sauce in pan for 3 minutes and serve with chicken.

title: Basil Egg Toast
description: A simple breakfast toast with basil aroma.
directions: Toast bread lightly. Cook eggs in butter in a pan on low heat. Add basil, salt, and black pepper. Place eggs on bread and serve warm.

title: Mushroom Noodle Stir
description: A quick noodle dish with mushroom flavor.
directions: Boil noodles and strain. Cook onion and mushroom in oil 5 minutes. Add soy sauce and black pepper. Stir in noodles and cook 2 minutes before serving.

title: Potato Pepper Bake
description: A simple roasted potato and pepper dish.
directions: Set oven to 200C. Mix potato and red pepper with olive oil, salt, thyme, and black pepper. Spread on tray and bake 25 minutes, stirring once. Serve hot.

title: Lime Shrimp Saute
description: A zesty shrimp dish with citrus aroma.
directions: Heat oil and cook garlic 1 minute. Add shrimp and cook 3 minutes. Add lime juice, salt, and black pepper. Cook 2 more minutes and serve.

title: Herb Lemon Chicken
description: A simple citrus chicken dish with mild herb aroma.
directions: Mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, basil, salt, and black pepper. Coat chicken and rest 20 minutes. Heat a pan on medium and cook chicken 6 to 7 minutes on each side. Let rest 2 minutes before serving.

title: Tomato Basil Soup
description: A smooth tomato soup with light basil flavor.
directions: Cook onion in olive oil for 3 minutes. Add tomato and stir for 5 minutes. Add 2 cups water and simmer 15 minutes. Add basil, salt, and black pepper. Blend until smooth and heat 2 more minutes.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp
description: A quick shrimp saute in garlic butter.
directions: Melt butter on medium heat. Add garlic and cook 1 minute. Add shrimp and cook 3 minutes. Add lemon juice, salt, and black pepper. Cook 2 more minutes and serve warm.

title: Mushroom Rice Bowl
description: A simple rice bowl with mushroom aroma.
directions: Cook rice in water. Saute onion and mushroom in oil for 5 minutes. Add soy sauce and black pepper. Mix rice into pan and heat 2 minutes before serving.

title: Spinach Egg Scramble
description: A simple egg scramble with spinach.
directions: Melt butter in a pan. Add spinach and cook 1 minute. Add eggs, salt, and black pepper. Stir on low heat for 3 minutes until set.

title: Honey Soy Noodles
description: Sweet and savory noodles with soy and honey.
directions: Boil noodles. Saute onion in oil 3 minutes. Add soy sauce, honey, and black pepper. Stir in noodles and cook 2 minutes.

title: Basil Chicken Pasta
description: Pasta with chicken and basil in a light sauce.
directions: Boil pasta. Cook chicken in oil for 6 minutes. Add basil and salt. Mix with pasta and parmesan, heat 1 minute, and serve.

title: Potato Carrot Bake
description: A roasted mix of potato and carrot.
directions: Heat oven to 200C. Mix vegetables with oil, thyme, salt, and pepper. Bake 25 minutes, stirring once.

title: Lime Rice
description: A light rice dish with lime aroma.
directions: Cook rice. Mix with lime juice, olive oil, salt, and basil. Heat 1 minute before serving.

title: Bean Pasta Salad
description: A cold pasta salad with beans and simple dressing.
directions: Boil pasta and cool. Mix with beans, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Chill 10 minutes before serving.

title: Egg Tomato Skillet
description: A simple egg dish cooked with tomato.
directions: Cook tomato in oil 3 minutes. Add eggs, salt, and black pepper. Cook on low heat 4 minutes until set.

title: Carrot Ginger Soup
description: A warm smooth soup with ginger aroma.
directions: Cook onion and carrot in oil 5 minutes. Add 3 cups water and ginger. Simmer 15 minutes. Blend and heat 2 minutes with salt and pepper.

title: Olive Pasta
description: A light pasta dish with olive flavor.
directions: Boil pasta. Heat olive oil and olives 2 minutes. Add basil and salt. Mix pasta and stir 1 minute before serving.

title: Coconut Rice
description: A creamy rice dish made with coconut milk.
directions: Mix rice, coconut milk, water, salt, and sugar in a pot. Cook on low heat 15 minutes until soft. Rest 5 minutes and serve.

title: Garlic Potato Mash
description: A simple mashed potato with garlic.
directions: Boil potatoes 15 minutes. Mash with butter, milk, garlic, and salt. Heat 1 minute and serve.

title: Soy Ginger Chicken
description: A chicken dish with soy and ginger glaze.
directions: Mix soy sauce, ginger, and honey. Cook chicken in oil 7 minutes per side. Add sauce and simmer 5 minutes.

title: Cinnamon Oat Bowl
description: A warm oat bowl with light cinnamon flavor.
directions: Cook oats with water, salt, and cinnamon for 5 minutes on low heat. Stir in sugar and serve.

title: Tomato Olive Toast
description: A simple toast with tomato and olive topping.
directions: Toast bread lightly. Mix tomato, olive, olive oil, and salt. Spoon mixture on bread and serve.

title: Lentil Stew
description: A warm lentil stew with mild seasoning.
directions: Cook onion and carrot in oil 3 minutes. Add lentil and 3 cups water. Simmer 20 minutes. Add salt and black pepper and cook 3 more minutes.

title: Saffron Rice Bowl
description: Light and aromatic rice served with a warm golden hue.
directions: Heat olive oil in a pot and cook onion and garlic for 3 minutes. Add rice and stir for 2 minutes. Warm water separately and dissolve saffron in it. Pour the saffron water into the pot and add salt. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover, and cook for 15 minutes on low heat. Let it rest for 5 minutes before serving.

title: Beef Chili Stew
description: A hearty and warming stew with tender beef and rich spice.
directions: Heat a pot and brown the beef for 5 minutes. Add onion and cook 3 more minutes. Add tomato and cook until softened. Mix in chili powder, salt, and black pepper. Add beans and water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 35 minutes until the beef is tender. Rest for 5 minutes before serving.

title: Spicy Quinoa Stuffed Peppers
description: Colorful bell peppers filled with a hearty quinoa mixture spiced with cumin and chili. This nutritious dish bursts with flavor for a wholesome meal.
directions: Cook quinoa as per package, rinsing first and simmering in 2 cups water for 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 190C. Halve peppers lengthwise, remove seeds. Chop onion and saute until soft, about 3 minutes. Add cooked quinoa, beans, corn, cumin, and chili powder; stir in tomato sauce and heat through. Fill pepper halves with mixture. Bake covered for 20 minutes, then uncovered 5 minutes more until tender.

title: Creamy Mushroom Risotto
description: Silky arborio rice simmered with earthy mushrooms and parmesan.
directions: Warm broth in a saucepan over low heat. Dice onion and slice mushrooms. Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a pan over medium heat. Saute onion until translucent, 4 minutes, then add mushrooms and cook until browned, 5 minutes. Stir in rice for 2 minutes, add wine and stir until absorbed. Add broth ladle by ladle, stirring until absorbed, about 20 minutes total. Off heat, stir in remaining butter and parmesan. Serve immediately.

title: Mango Coconut Chia Pudding
description: A tropical twist on chia pudding layered with sweet mango and creamy coconut milk. Ideal for a refreshing breakfast or light snack.
directions: Whisk chia seeds, coconut milk, honey, and vanilla in a bowl. Refrigerate covered for at least 4 hours or overnight, stirring halfway. Peel and dice mango, toss with lime juice. Layer pudding and mango in glasses. Zest lime on top and serve chilled.

title: Beef and Broccoli Stir-Fry
description: Tender beef slices tossed with crisp broccoli in a savory soy-ginger sauce.
directions: Slice beef thinly after partial freezing for ease. Marinate in soy sauce, ginger, minced garlic, brown sugar, and cornstarch for 15 minutes. Cut broccoli into florets and blanch in boiling water 2 minutes, then ice bath. Heat sesame oil in wok over high heat. Stir-fry beef until browned, 3 minutes, remove. Add broccoli, stir-fry 2 minutes, return beef and toss until sauce thickens. Serve over rice.

title: Avocado Toast with Poached Eggs
description: Crispy toast topped with creamy smashed avocado and runny poached eggs. A simple, protein-packed breakfast.
directions: Toast bread slices until golden. Halve avocados, scoop flesh, mash with lemon juice, salt, and pepper. For eggs, simmer water in pan with splash of vinegar. Crack eggs into ramekins, slide into water, poach 3 minutes for runny yolks. Drain on towel. Spread avocado on toast, top with eggs, sprinkle red pepper flakes. Serve right away.

title: Greek Yogurt Parfait
description: Layers of tangy Greek yogurt, crunchy granola, and fresh berries.
directions: Rinse and slice strawberries, rinse blueberries. Chop almonds. In glasses, layer yogurt, then 2 tablespoons granola, then berries. Drizzle honey over layers. Repeat once more. Top with almonds. Serve chilled.

title: Salmon Teriyaki Bowl
description: Flaky salmon glazed in sweet teriyaki sauce over steamed rice and veggies. A balanced Japanese-inspired meal ready in under 30 minutes.
directions: Rinse rice, cook with 1.5 cups water, simmer covered 15 minutes. Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, grated ginger; simmer 2 minutes for sauce. Cut broccoli into florets, steam 4 minutes. Preheat oven to 200C. Pat salmon dry, brush with half sauce, bake 12 minutes, basting midway. Toast sesame seeds 1 minute. Assemble bowls: rice, broccoli, salmon, drizzle remaining sauce, top with seeds.

title: Lentil Soup with Carrots
description: Warm and nourishing red lentil soup loaded with carrots and cumin. Perfect for chilly evenings.
directions: Rinse lentils until water clears. Dice carrots and chop onion. Heat olive oil in pot, saute onion and carrots 6 minutes until soft. Add cumin, stir 30 seconds. Add lentils, broth; boil then simmer covered 20 minutes until tender. Blend half for creaminess. Stir in lemon juice and salt. Simmer 2 minutes more and serve hot.

title: Veggie Packed Minestrone Soup
description: Hearty Italian soup brimming with seasonal vegetables, beans, and pasta in a tomato broth.
directions: Dice tomatoes, carrots, and zucchini. Heat olive oil in pot over medium, saute vegetables 5 minutes until soft. Add vegetable broth and white beans, bring to boil. Stir in pasta and basil, simmer 10 minutes until pasta is tender. Season with salt if needed and serve hot with bread.

title: Berry Almond Smoothie Bowl
description: Thick blended berries and yogurt topped with crunchy almonds and granola.
directions: Blend mixed berries, greek yogurt, almond milk, and banana until smooth and thick. Pour into bowl. Top with granola, chopped almonds, and a drizzle of honey. Serve immediately for best texture.

title: French Onion Soup Gratinee
description: Rich caramelized onions in beef broth topped with cheesy baguette slices.
directions: Slice onions thinly. Melt butter in pot over medium-low, cook onions with thyme 30 minutes until caramelized, stirring occasionally. Deglaze with white wine, cook 2 minutes. Add beef broth, simmer 20 minutes. Preheat broiler. Ladle soup into bowls, top with baguette slices and gruyere. Broil 2 minutes until bubbly and golden.

title: Quinoa Salad with Feta and Cucumber
description: Fluffy quinoa mixed with crisp cucumber, tangy feta, and lemon vinaigrette. A light Mediterranean side or lunch.
directions: Cook quinoa in 2 cups water for 15 minutes, fluff and cool. Dice cucumber and halve tomatoes. Crumble feta and chop mint. Whisk olive oil and lemon juice for dressing. Toss all together in bowl. Chill 10 minutes before serving.

title: Falafel Pita Pockets
description: Crispy chickpea falafel stuffed in pita with tahini and veggies. Middle Eastern street food at home.
directions: Mash chickpeas with chopped parsley, cumin, and half the olive oil into paste. Form into balls, fry in remaining oil 3 minutes per side until golden. Slice tomato and cucumber. Mix tahini with water to thin. Stuff pita with falafel, veggies, and tahini. Serve fresh.

title: Vegetable Stir-Fry Noodles
description: Colorful mixed vegetables tossed with rice noodles in a light soy-ginger sauce. A quick vegan stir-fry packed with crunch and umami.
directions: Cook rice noodles according to package, drain and rinse with cold water. Slice carrot, bell pepper, and broccoli into thin strips. Heat sesame oil in wok over high heat. Add ginger and vegetables, stir-fry 4 minutes until crisp-tender. Toss in noodles and soy sauce, stir 2 minutes to coat. Garnish with sliced green onions and serve hot.

title: Turkey Meatballs in Tomato Sauce
description: Juicy turkey meatballs simmered in a simple herbed tomato sauce. Comforting Italian-American fare for any night.
directions: Mix ground turkey, bread crumbs, egg, half the parmesan, minced garlic, and oregano; form into 1-inch balls. Heat olive oil in skillet over medium, brown meatballs 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce, simmer covered 15 minutes until cooked through. Sprinkle with remaining parmesan and serve over pasta.

title: Lamb Kofta Kebabs
description: Spiced ground lamb skewers grilled to perfection. Turkish street food with yogurt dip.
directions: Grate onion and mince garlic, mix with ground lamb, spices, and chopped parsley. Form into sausage shapes around skewers. Brush with olive oil, grill 4 minutes per side until browned. Mix yogurt with garlic for dip. Serve kebabs with dip and flatbread.

title: Spaghetti Carbonara
description: Classic Roman pasta with eggs, cheese, and pancetta for creamy indulgence.
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente, reserve 1 cup water, drain. Dice pancetta, fry in olive oil until crisp, 5 minutes. Beat eggs with parmesan and black pepper. Toss hot pasta with pancetta and egg mixture, add pasta water to emulsify. Serve immediately.

title: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Rich mushroom sauce over egg noodles with sour cream tang.
directions: Cook egg noodles, drain. Slice mushrooms and onion. Melt butter in skillet, saute onion 3 minutes, add mushrooms 5 minutes until browned. Sprinkle flour, stir 1 minute. Add beef broth and mustard, simmer 5 minutes. Stir in sour cream off heat. Serve over noodles.

title: Coconut Shrimp Curry
description: Succulent shrimp in a mild coconut curry with Indian spices.
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Chop onion and tomatoes, grate ginger. Heat olive oil, saute onion and ginger 4 minutes. Add curry powder, stir 30 seconds. Add tomatoes, cook 5 minutes. Stir in coconut milk and shrimp, simmer 5 minutes until pink. Garnish with cilantro and serve with rice.

title: Baked Ratatouille
description: Layered summer vegetables in tomato sauce, Provencal style.
directions: Preheat oven to 180C. Slice vegetables thinly. Spread tomato sauce in baking dish, layer vegetables alternately, tuck in minced garlic and thyme. Drizzle olive oil, season with salt. Cover and bake 40 minutes, uncover last 10 minutes until tender.

title: Butternut Squash Soup
description: Velvety roasted squash soup with nutmeg warmth.
directions: Preheat oven to 200C. Cube squash, toss with olive oil, roast 25 minutes. Saute chopped onion and grated ginger 4 minutes. Add roasted squash and broth, simmer 10 minutes. Blend smooth, stir in coconut milk and nutmeg. Heat through and serve.

title: Chicken Shawarma Wraps
description: Marinated chicken in spiced yogurt wrap with veggies.
directions: Slice chicken, marinate in yogurt, minced garlic, cumin, paprika 30 minutes. Grill or saute 6 minutes per side. Slice cucumber and tomato. Warm pita, fill with chicken and veggies. Serve with extra yogurt.

title: Beef Bulgogi
