description: Thinly sliced beef marinated in sweet soy sauce, Korean style.
directions: Slice beef thin. Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, sesame oil, minced garlic, grated ginger. Marinate beef 20 minutes. Cook rice. Stir-fry beef 3 minutes until caramelized. Add sliced green onions. Serve over rice.

title: Lentil Dal
description: Simple spiced lentils simmered with garlic and cumin.
directions: Rinse lentils. Chop onion and tomato, mince garlic. Saute onion and garlic in oil 4 minutes. Add spices, stir 30 seconds. Add lentils, tomato, broth; simmer 20 minutes until soft. Garnish with cilantro. Serve with rice.

title: Eggplant Parmesan
description: Breaded eggplant baked with marinara and mozzarella.
directions: Slice eggplant, salt and drain 20 minutes. Beat eggs. Dip slices in egg then bread crumbs mixed with parmesan. Fry in olive oil 3 minutes per side. Layer in dish with sauce and mozzarella. Bake at 180C 25 minutes. Top with basil.

title: Avocado Egg Boats
description: Baked eggs in avocado halves for a nutritious brunch.
directions: Halve avocados, remove pits, scoop slightly for egg space. Crack egg into each. Dice tomato, sprinkle with salt, pepper. Bake at 200C 15 minutes until eggs set. Top with chives and tomato.

title: Sweet Potato Fries with Aioli
description: Crispy baked sweet potato fries dipped in garlicky aioli.
directions: Preheat oven to 220C. Cut sweet potatoes into fries, toss with olive oil, paprika, salt. Bake 25 minutes, flip halfway. Mince garlic, mix with mayonnaise and lemon juice for aioli. Serve fries with dip.

title: Couscous with Roasted Vegetables
description: Fluffy couscous topped with roasted seasonal veggies.
directions: Preheat oven to 200C. Chop veggies, toss with olive oil and cumin, roast 20 minutes. Cook couscous in boiling water 5 minutes, fluff. Squeeze lemon over couscous. Top with veggies and chopped parsley.

title: Turkey Chili
description: Hearty turkey chili with beans and bold spices.
directions: Chop onion and tomatoes. Heat olive oil, brown turkey 5 minutes. Add onion, cook 3 minutes. Stir in spices, tomatoes, beans, broth. Simmer 20 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: Cauliflower Buffalo Wings
description: Crispy baked cauliflower florets in spicy buffalo sauce.
directions: Preheat oven to 220C. Cut cauliflower into florets. Mix flour, milk, garlic powder for batter, coat florets. Bake 20 minutes. Melt butter with hot sauce, toss baked florets in sauce. Bake 5 minutes more. Serve with ranch.

title: Salmon Cakes
description: Flaky canned salmon patties with lemon herb mayo.
directions: Drain salmon, mix with bread crumbs, egg, half mayo, lemon zest, dill, salt. Form patties. Fry in olive oil 3 minutes per side. Mix remaining mayo with lemon juice for sauce. Serve cakes with sauce.

title: Breakfast Burrito
description: Scrambled eggs, beans, and cheese in a tortilla wrap.
directions: Scramble eggs in olive oil. Warm tortilla, layer eggs, beans, cheese, sliced avocado, salsa. Roll up tightly. Serve warm.

title: Strawberry Spinach Salad
description: Sweet strawberries with spinach, nuts, and balsamic dressing.
directions: Slice strawberries, toast almonds. Whisk balsamic, olive oil, honey, salt for dressing. Toss spinach, strawberries, almonds with dressing. Serve immediately.

title: Shrimp Scampi
description: Garlicky shrimp in white wine butter sauce over pasta.
directions: Cook linguine, drain. Saute minced garlic in butter 1 minute, add shrimp and flakes, cook 3 minutes. Add wine, simmer 2 minutes. Toss with pasta, lemon juice, chopped parsley. Serve hot.

title: Pad Thai
description: Stir-fried rice noodles with tofu, eggs, and tamarind sauce.
directions: Soak noodles in hot water 10 minutes, drain. Mix tamarind, fish sauce, sugar for sauce. Stir-fry tofu 2 minutes, push aside, scramble eggs. Add noodles, sauce, sprouts; toss 3 minutes. Top with peanuts and lime.

title: Vegetable Fried Rice
description: Day-old rice stir-fried with mixed veggies and soy.
directions: Dice carrot, chop green onions, grate ginger. Heat sesame oil, scramble eggs, remove. Stir-fry ginger, carrot, peas 3 minutes. Add rice, soy sauce, eggs; toss 4 minutes. Stir in green onions.

title: Baba Ghanoush
description: Smoky roasted eggplant dip with tahini and garlic.
directions: Roast eggplant at 220C 30 minutes until soft, cool, scoop flesh. Blend with minced garlic, tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, cumin, salt. Chill. Garnish with parsley, serve with pita.

title: Cottage Cheese Pancakes
description: Fluffy high-protein pancakes with cottage cheese.
directions: Blend cottage cheese, eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla smooth. Heat butter in pan. Pour batter for pancakes, cook 2 minutes per side. Top with blueberries. Serve warm.

title: Chicken Fajitas
description: Sizzling chicken and peppers in warm tortillas.
directions: Slice chicken and veggies. Season chicken with cumin, chili powder. Heat olive oil, stir-fry chicken 5 minutes, add peppers and onion 4 minutes. Squeeze lime over. Serve in warmed tortillas.

title: Creamy Hummus
description: Smooth chickpea dip with garlic and lemon.
directions: Drain chickpeas, reserve liquid. Blend chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, minced garlic, olive oil, cumin, salt with aquafaba for creaminess. Chill. Garnish with paprika and oil, serve with veggies.

title: Broccoli Cheddar Soup
description: Cheesy broccoli soup blended creamy.
directions: Chop broccoli and onion. Melt butter, stir in flour 1 minute. Add broth, milk, nutmeg, simmer. Add veggies, cook 10 minutes. Blend half, stir in cheese until melted. Serve hot.

title: Stuffed Peppers
description: Rice and ground beef stuffed in bell peppers.
directions: Cook rice. Halve peppers, remove seeds. Brown beef with chopped onion in oil 5 minutes. Mix with rice, half sauce, cumin. Stuff peppers. Bake at 180C 30 minutes covered, top with cheese, 10 minutes more.

title: Berry Smoothie
description: Blended frozen berries with yogurt and banana.
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. Add more milk if too thick. Pour into glass, top with extra chia. Serve chilled.

title: Beef Stroganoff
description: Tender beef strips in mushroom sour cream sauce.
directions: Cook noodles. Slice beef and mushrooms, chop onion. Brown beef in butter 3 minutes, remove. Saute onion and mushrooms 5 minutes. Sprinkle flour, add broth, simmer. Stir in sour cream, return beef. Serve over noodles.

title: Blue Cheese Dressing
description: Chunky blue cheese dip for wings or salad.
directions: Crumble cheese, mix with mayo, sour cream, lemon juice, garlic powder, salt, pepper. Stir in chopped chives. Chill 30 minutes. Serve with veggies or chips.

title: Risotto Milanese
description: Saffron-infused rice with parmesan.
directions: Steep saffron in warm broth. Saute onion in oil and butter, add rice 2 minutes. Deglaze with wine. Add broth ladle by ladle, stirring 18 minutes. Stir in parmesan.

title: Stuffed Mushrooms
description: Baked mushroom caps filled with spinach and feta.
directions: Remove mushroom stems, chop. Saute stems, spinach, minced garlic in oil 3 minutes. Mix with feta, bread crumbs, lemon juice, salt. Stuff caps. Bake at 180C 15 minutes.

title: Bell Pepper Gazpacho
description: Chilled blended soup of ripe tomatoes, cucumbers, and bell peppers with a Spanish flair.
directions: Roughly chop tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, onion, and garlic. Blend all with olive oil, vinegar, and salt until smooth. Chill at least 2 hours. Serve garnished with diced veggies.

title: Balsamic Grilled Asparagus
description: Tender asparagus spears grilled with balsamic glaze.
directions: Trim asparagus. Toss with olive oil, salt, pepper. Grill 4 minutes, turning once. Drizzle reduced balsamic. Shave parmesan over top.

title: Sauteed Spinach
description: Wilted spinach with garlic and lemon.
directions: Heat olive oil, saute minced garlic and flakes 30 seconds. Add spinach in batches, wilt 2 minutes. Squeeze lemon, season with salt. Serve warm.

title: Creamed Corn
description: Sweet corn in a creamy herb sauce.
directions: Melt butter, add corn, cream, sugar, salt, pepper; simmer 5 minutes until thickened. Stir in chopped parsley. Serve hot.

title: Ratatouille
description: Stewed summer vegetables in Provencal herbs.
directions: Dice vegetables. Saute onion and garlic in olive oil 3 minutes. Add peppers, eggplant, zucchini; cook 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes and thyme, simmer 15 minutes. Season and serve.

title: Baked Zucchini Chips
description: Crispy zucchini slices seasoned with herbs.
directions: Preheat oven to 220C. Slice zucchini thinly. Toss with oil, salt, pepper, oregano. Bake on sheet 20 minutes, flip, sprinkle parmesan, bake 5 more minutes.

title: Cauliflower Mash
description: Low-carb mashed cauliflower with butter and chives.
directions: Steam cauliflower florets 10 minutes. Blend with roasted garlic, butter, warm milk, salt, pepper until smooth. Stir in chives.

title: Deviled Eggs
description: Classic hard-boiled eggs filled with creamy yolk mixture.
directions: Boil eggs 10 minutes, cool, halve. Mash yolks with mayo, mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper. Pipe into whites. Garnish with paprika and chives.

title: Guacamole
description: Fresh avocado dip with lime and cilantro.
directions: Mash avocados with lime juice. Dice tomato, onion, jalapeno, mince garlic and cilantro. Mix all, season with salt. Serve with chips.

title: Bruschetta
description: Toasted bread topped with tomato basil relish.
directions: Dice tomatoes, chop basil. Mix with olive oil, balsamic, salt. Slice and toast baguette, rub with garlic. Top with tomato mixture.

title: Ceviche
description: Citrus-marinated shrimp with onions and cilantro.
directions: Chop shrimp finely. Mix with lime and orange juice, diced onion, minced jalapeno, chopped cilantro, salt. Marinate 30 minutes in fridge. Serve chilled.

title: Buffalo Wings
description: Spicy baked chicken wings with blue cheese.
directions: Toss wings with oil, salt, pepper. Bake at 200C 40 minutes, flip halfway. Melt butter with hot sauce, toss wings in. Serve with celery and blue cheese dip.

title: Tuna Tartare
description: Diced tuna with soy, ginger, and avocado.
directions: Dice tuna and avocado finely. Mix with grated ginger, soy, sesame oil, chopped green onion, lime juice, salt. Chill 10 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: Stuffed Jalapenos
description: Cream cheese filled jalapenos wrapped in bacon.
directions: Halve jalapenos, remove seeds. Mix cream cheese, cheddar, salt, pepper. Stuff halves. Halve bacon, wrap around, secure with toothpick. Bake at 190C 20 minutes.

title: Veggie Platter
description: Fresh cut vegetables with yogurt dip.
directions: Cut veggies into sticks. Mix yogurt, lemon juice, chopped dill, salt for dip. Arrange veggies around dip bowl.

title: Meatballs
description: Italian-style meatballs in marinara.
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg, parmesan, minced garlic, salt. Form small balls. Brown in oil 5 minutes. Simmer in marinara 10 minutes. Serve with toothpicks.

title: Chips and Salsa
description: Homemade tortilla chips with fresh tomato salsa.
directions: Dice tomato, onion, jalapeno, chop cilantro. Mix with lime juice, salt for salsa. Cut tortillas into triangles, brush with oil, bake at 180C 10 minutes. Serve together.

title: French Onion Soup
description: Caramelized onions in beef broth with gruyere croutons.
directions: Slice onions, caramelize in butter with thyme 30 minutes. Deglaze with wine. Add broth, simmer 20 minutes. Top bowls with toasted baguette and gruyere, broil until bubbly.

title: Chicken Noodle Soup
description: Comforting broth with shredded chicken and noodles.
directions: Cook chicken in broth 20 minutes, shred. Saute diced carrot, celery, onion in oil 5 minutes. Add broth, noodles, chicken, salt; simmer 10 minutes.

title: Gazpacho
description: Cold Spanish soup of blended veggies.
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. Chill 2 hours. Garnish with diced veggies. Serve cold.

title: Tortilla Soup
description: Spicy chicken soup with tortilla strips.
directions: Cook chicken in broth 15 minutes, shred. Blend tomatoes, onion with some broth. Fry tortilla strips. Simmer blended mix in broth, add chicken. Top with avocado, lime, cilantro, strips.

title: Lentil Soup
description: Earthy red lentil soup with cumin.
directions: Saute diced onion and carrot in oil 5 minutes. Add cumin, lentils, broth; simmer 20 minutes. Blend half, add lemon juice, salt.

title: Carrot Ginger Soup
description: Velvety spiced carrot soup.
directions: Saute onion and grated ginger in oil 4 minutes. Add diced carrots, cumin, broth; simmer 20 minutes. Blend, stir in coconut milk, salt. Heat through.

title: Beef Stroganoff
description: Tender beef strips in a creamy mushroom sauce served over noodles.
directions: Slice beef and mushrooms, chop onion. Brown beef in butter 3 minutes, remove. Saute onion and mushrooms 5 minutes. Sprinkle flour, add broth, simmer. Stir in sour cream off heat, return beef. Cook noodles, serve stroganoff over top.

title: Falafel Wrap
description: Crispy chickpea patties in pita with tahini and veggies.
directions: Mash chickpeas with chopped parsley, cumin. Form patties, fry in oil 3 minutes per side. Thin tahini with water. Slice veggies. Stuff pita with falafel, veggies, tahini.

title: Berry Parfait
description: Layered yogurt, granola, and fresh berries.
directions: Layer yogurt, granola, berries in glasses. Drizzle honey between layers. Top with chopped almonds. Serve chilled.

title: Shakshuka
description: Poached eggs in spicy tomato sauce.
directions: Saute diced onion and pepper in oil 5 minutes. Add spices, chopped tomatoes, simmer 10 minutes. Make wells, crack eggs in, cover 5 minutes until set. Crumble feta over top.

title: Omelette
description: Fluffy three-egg omelette with cheese and herbs.
directions: Whisk eggs with salt, pepper. Melt butter in pan, pour eggs, tilt to spread. Sprinkle cheese and chives when edges set. Fold, cook 1 minute more.

title: Cottage Cheese Bowl
description: High-protein cottage cheese with tomatoes and basil.
directions: Dice tomato, chop basil. Mix cottage cheese with salt, pepper. Top with tomato and basil, drizzle oil. Serve fresh.

title: Lemon Herb Chicken
description: Juicy roasted chicken breasts marinated in lemon, garlic and fresh herbs.
directions: Whisk lemon juice, oil, minced garlic, thyme, and salt. Marinate chicken 20 minutes. Roast at 200 Celsius for 20-25 minutes until cooked through. Let rest 5 minutes and serve.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp
description: Quick skillet shrimp in a garlic butter sauce, perfect with rice or pasta.
directions: Melt butter in a skillet, add minced garlic and cook 1 minute. Add shrimp and cook 2-3 minutes per side until pink. Squeeze lemon over shrimp, stir in parsley and season with salt. Serve immediately.

title: Spinach Frittata
description: Baked eggs with spinach and cheese, great for brunch.
directions: Preheat oven to 180 Celsius. Whisk together eggs, milk, salt and pepper until smooth. Saute the spinach in a little oil until wilted, then combine with eggs and grated parmesan in an ovenproof skillet. Bake for 20-25 minutes until the center is set and golden; let rest 5 minutes before slicing.

title: Lentil Soup
description: Hearty lentil soup with carrots and tomatoes, comforting and nutritious.
directions: Heat olive oil in a large pot and saute diced onion, garlic and carrot until softened. Add rinsed lentils and chopped tomato, then cover with 4 cups of water or broth. Bring to a simmer and cook for 25-30 minutes until lentils are tender. Puree part of the soup for a creamier texture if desired, adjust seasoning and serve hot with a squeeze of lemon.

title: Banana Oat Pancakes
description: Simple pancakes using mashed banana and oats - no flour needed.
directions: Blend the oats into a coarse flour, then mix with mashed banana, egg, milk, cinnamon and baking powder until combined. Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and lightly grease. Spoon batter to form small pancakes and cook 2-3 minutes per side until golden and cooked through. Keep warm and serve stacked with fruit or a drizzle of syrup.

title: Teriyaki Tofu Bowl
description: Crispy pan-fried tofu glazed in homemade teriyaki, served over rice and steamed veg.
directions: Press tofu to remove excess water, cube and toss in a little cornstarch for crisping. Pan-fry the cubes in oil until golden on all sides. Make a teriyaki glaze by simmering soy sauce, mirin and sugar until slightly thickened, then toss the tofu in the glaze to coat. Serve the glazed tofu over rice with sliced green onions and steamed vegetables.

title: Apple Oat Muffins
description: Moist muffins made with oats and diced apples, wholesome and easy.
directions: Preheat oven to 180 Celsius and line a muffin tin. Mix oats, diced apple, egg, milk, sugar and baking powder until just combined. Spoon batter into the tin filling each cup about three-quarters full. Bake 18-22 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean; cool slightly before removing from the tin.

title: Mango Salsa
description: Fresh mango salsa brightened with lime and cilantro - great with chips or fish.
directions: Dice the mango and red onion into small, even pieces. Finely chop the jalapeno (remove seeds for less heat) and cilantro, then combine with mango and onion. Squeeze fresh lime juice over the mixture and season with salt; stir and let sit 10 minutes to allow flavors to meld. Serve chilled with tortilla chips or as a topping for grilled fish.

title: Vegetable Curry
description: Mixed vegetable curry simmered in coconut-flavored sauce, hearty and warming.
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil until translucent, then add diced potato and carrot and cook a few minutes. Stir in curry powder to bloom the spices, then pour in coconut milk and add peas. Simmer gently until all vegetables are tender and the sauce has thickened slightly. Adjust salt and serve with steamed rice or flatbread.

title: Herbed Quinoa Salad
description: Bright quinoa salad with fresh herbs and a lemony dressing.
directions: Rinse and cook the quinoa according to package instructions, then let it cool. Dice cucumber and tomato and finely chop parsley. Whisk lemon juice with olive oil and salt to make a bright dressing, then toss with the quinoa and vegetables. Chill for 20 minutes to let flavors meld; serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: Roasted Garlic Salmon
description: Oven-roasted salmon with a golden garlic-lemon crust.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 Celsius. Mince garlic and combine with lemon zest, olive oil, parsley, salt and pepper. Place salmon on a baking sheet, spread the garlic mixture on top and roast for 12-15 minutes until flaky. Let rest 3 minutes, then squeeze fresh lemon juice over the fish before serving.

title: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Creamy mushroom stroganoff served over warm pasta.
directions: Cook pasta until al dente and set aside. Saute sliced mushrooms and onions in butter until browned, add garlic and cook briefly. Stir in sour cream and a splash of pasta water to create a silky sauce, season with salt. Combine with the drained pasta and serve topped with extra black pepper.

title: Spicy Chickpea Wrap
description: Warm spiced chickpeas wrapped with cooling yogurt and fresh veggies.
directions: Toss chickpeas with chili powder, a little oil and salt, then warm in a skillet until slightly crispy. Mix yogurt with a squeeze of lemon to make a cooling sauce. Fill tortillas with lettuce, sliced cucumber, spiced chickpeas and a drizzle of yogurt. Roll and serve immediately.

title: Herb Roasted Veggies
description: Colorful oven-roasted vegetables seasoned with fresh herbs.
directions: Preheat oven to 200 Celsius. Chop all vegetables into even-sized pieces, toss with olive oil, thyme, salt and pepper, then spread on a baking sheet. Roast for 25-30 minutes until tender and caramelized, tossing once halfway through. Serve warm as a hearty side.

title: Shrimp Scampi
description: Garlicky shrimp served over pasta with a bright lemon finish.
directions: Cook the pasta until al dente. In a large skillet, melt butter and saute minced garlic until fragrant. Add shrimp and cook 2-3 minutes per side until opaque, then squeeze in lemon juice and stir in chopped parsley. Toss the pasta with the shrimp and sauce, adjust seasoning, and serve immediately.

title: Tomato Basil Soup
description: Comforting creamy tomato soup balanced with fresh basil.
directions: Saute chopped onion and garlic in olive oil until translucent. Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they begin to break down, then add vegetable broth and simmer 15-20 minutes. Stir in chopped basil, then blend the soup until smooth; return to heat, adjust seasoning and simmer a few minutes more. Serve hot with a drizzle of olive oil and extra basil leaves.

title: Chicken Caesar Wrap
description: A handheld Caesar with grilled chicken, romaine and parmesan.
directions: Grill or pan-sear the seasoned chicken until cooked through, then slice thinly. Toss romaine with caesar dressing, parmesan and croutons. Place the salad and sliced chicken on tortillas, wrap tightly and serve warm or chilled.

title: Black Bean & Corn Salad
description: A zesty, colorful salad with black beans, corn and fresh herbs.
directions: Combine drained black beans and cooked corn in a bowl with diced red pepper and finely chopped red onion. Chop cilantro and squeeze fresh lime juice over the mixture; drizzle with olive oil and toss to combine. Let sit 10-15 minutes for flavors to meld, then serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: Stuffed Peppers
description: Bell peppers stuffed with seasoned rice and meat, baked with cheese on top.
directions: Cook the rice and let cool slightly. Brown ground beef with diced onion until cooked, stir in chopped tomato and seasoning, then mix with rice. Hollow out bell peppers and stuff them with the meat and rice mixture. Top with cheddar and bake at 190 Celsius for 25-30 minutes until peppers are tender and cheese is melted.

title: Garlic Lemon Kale
description: Quick sauteed kale with bright lemon and garlic flavors.
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and add minced garlic, cooking until fragrant. Add chopped kale and saute until wilted but still bright green. Finish with a squeeze of lemon juice, season with salt and pepper and serve immediately as a nutritious side.

title: Teriyaki Salmon Bowl
description: Sticky-sweet teriyaki salmon served over rice with veggies and sesame.
directions: Whisk soy sauce and honey to make a quick teriyaki glaze. Sear or bake the salmon and brush with glaze until caramelized. Serve the salmon over steamed rice with blanched broccoli, sprinkle sesame seeds and sliced green onion on top.

title: Pumpkin Spice Oatmeal
description: Warm spiced oatmeal with pumpkin and warming spices.
directions: Cook oats with milk according to package instructions, stirring in pumpkin puree and spices halfway through. Sweeten with maple syrup and serve hot with an extra dash of cinnamon.

title: Greek Chicken Skewers
description: Marinated chicken skewers with lemon, garlic and oregano.
directions: Marinate cubed chicken in a mixture of yogurt, lemon juice, minced garlic, oregano and olive oil for at least 30 minutes. Thread onto skewers and grill or broil until cooked through and slightly charred. Serve with pita and a squeeze of extra lemon.

title: Egg Fried Rice
description: Quick fried rice with scrambled egg and vegetables - great for using leftovers.
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large skillet and scramble the eggs; remove and set aside. Stir-fry diced carrot and peas until tender, add cooked rice and soy sauce and toss to combine. Return scrambled eggs to the pan, fold in chopped green onions, adjust seasoning and serve hot.

title: Lemon Garlic Broccoli
description: Tender broccoli florets tossed with garlic and bright lemon.
directions: Steam or blanch broccoli until bright green and just tender, then immediately toss with olive oil, minced garlic and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper and serve warm as a simple, flavorful side.

title: Spiced Lentil Salad
description: Cold lentil salad with fresh herbs, citrus and a warm spice note.
directions: Cook lentils until tender and cool to room temperature. Dice cucumber, tomato and finely chop red onion and parsley. Toss lentils with vegetables, lemon juice and olive oil; season to taste and let rest for 10 minutes to allow flavors to meld. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: Blueberry Pancakes
description: Fluffy pancakes studded with fresh blueberries for a weekend treat.
directions: Whisk flour, baking powder and sugar, then mix in milk and egg until just combined. Fold in blueberries. Cook spoonfuls of batter on a hot greased griddle 2-3 minutes per side until golden. Serve stacked with butter and syrup.

title: Creamy Garlic Tuscan Shrimp
description: Succulent shrimp in a creamy garlic parmesan sauce with sun-dried tomatoes and spinach.
directions: Season shrimp with salt and pepper. Melt butter in skillet, cook shrimp 2 minutes per side, set aside. Add garlic, cook 1 minute. Pour cream, simmer 3 minutes. Add parmesan, stir until melted. Add spinach and sun-dried tomatoes. Return shrimp, toss to coat. Serve over pasta or rice.

title: Korean Beef Bulgogi
description: Thinly sliced marinated beef with sweet and savory Korean flavors, perfect for rice bowls.
directions: Slice beef thin against grain. Blend pear, soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, garlic for marinade. Marinate beef 2 hours minimum. Grill or pan-fry over high heat 2-3 minutes per side. Garnish with sliced scallions and sesame seeds. Serve with steamed rice and kimchi.

title: Shakshuka
description: Middle Eastern dish of poached eggs in spiced tomato sauce with peppers and onions.
directions: Saute diced onion and pepper in olive oil 5 minutes. Add cumin, paprika, cook 1 minute. Add crushed tomatoes, simmer 10 minutes. Make wells in sauce, crack eggs into wells. Cover, cook 8-10 minutes until eggs set. Garnish with fresh herbs and serve with crusty bread.

title: Black Bean Tacos
description: Hearty vegetarian tacos with seasoned black beans, fresh salsa, and creamy avocado.
directions: Heat black beans with cumin, salt, pepper. Warm tortillas. Mash avocado with lime juice and salt. Dice tomatoes, mix with cilantro. Assemble tacos with beans, avocado, tomato salsa. Squeeze lime juice on top and serve immediately.

title: Coconut Curry Lentils
description: Creamy vegan curry with red lentils simmered in coconut milk and aromatic spices.
directions: Saute onion 5 minutes. Add garlic, ginger, curry powder, cook 1 minute. Add lentils and broth, simmer 20 minutes. Stir in coconut milk, cook 10 more minutes until creamy. Season with salt. Serve over rice with fresh cilantro.

title: Caprese Salad
description: Classic Italian salad with fresh mozzarella, ripe tomatoes, and fragrant basil.
directions: Slice mozzarella and tomatoes into thick rounds. Arrange alternating slices on platter. Tuck fresh basil leaves between. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic reduction. Season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately at room temperature.

title: Banana Pancakes
description: Fluffy whole grain pancakes with mashed banana and warm maple syrup.
directions: Mash bananas. Whisk flour, baking powder, salt. Mix eggs, milk, melted butter, mashed banana. Combine wet and dry ingredients. Heat griddle, pour 1/4 cup batter per pancake. Cook until bubbles form, flip, cook 2 more minutes. Serve with maple syrup and sliced bananas.

title: Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: Colorful bell peppers filled with seasoned ground beef, rice, and melted cheese.
directions: Cook rice. Cut tops off peppers, remove seeds. Brown beef with onion and garlic. Mix beef, rice, half tomato sauce, half cheese. Fill peppers with mixture. Place in baking dish, pour remaining sauce around. Bake 180 Celsius 35 minutes. Top with cheese, bake 10 more minutes.

title: Spinach Artichoke Dip
description: Creamy warm dip with spinach, artichokes, and melted cheese, perfect for parties.
directions: Chop spinach and artichokes. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, half parmesan, garlic. Fold in spinach and artichokes. Transfer to baking dish, top with remaining parmesan. Bake 180 Celsius 25 minutes until bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips or bread.

title: Greek Yogurt Parfait
description: Layered breakfast parfait with creamy yogurt, crunchy granola, and fresh berries.
directions: Slice strawberries. In glasses or bowls, layer yogurt, granola, berries. Repeat layers. Drizzle with honey. Top with additional berries and a sprinkle of granola. Serve immediately for maximum crunch.

title: Beef Stroganoff
description: Russian classic with tender beef strips in creamy mushroom sauce over egg noodles.
directions: Slice beef thin, season. Brown in butter, set aside. Saute onion and mushrooms 8 minutes. Add broth, simmer 5 minutes. Reduce heat, stir in sour cream. Return beef, heat through. Serve over cooked egg noodles, garnish with parsley.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp Pasta
description: Quick pasta dish with succulent shrimp in garlic butter sauce and fresh parsley.
directions: Cook pasta al dente, reserve 1 cup pasta water. Melt butter, saute garlic 1 minute. Add shrimp, cook 3 minutes until pink. Add lemon juice, pepper flakes. Toss in pasta with some pasta water. Garnish with parsley and parmesan.

title: Apple Cinnamon Oatmeal
description: Warm and comforting oatmeal with sauteed apples and fragrant cinnamon.
directions: Dice apples, saute with cinnamon until soft. Cook oats in almond milk 5 minutes. Stir in maple syrup and half the apples. Top with remaining apples and chopped walnuts. Drizzle with extra maple syrup.

title: Eggplant Parmesan
description: Breaded eggplant slices baked with marinara sauce and melted mozzarella.
directions: Slice eggplant, salt, drain 30 minutes. Dip in beaten egg, then breadcrumbs. Bake at 200 Celsius 20 minutes. Layer in dish with marinara and mozzarella. Bake 25 minutes until bubbly. Top with parmesan, bake 5 more minutes.

title: Chicken Caesar Wrap
description: Grilled chicken with romaine lettuce and Caesar dressing in a flour tortilla.
directions: Grill seasoned chicken 6 minutes per side. Slice thin. Warm tortillas. Toss lettuce with dressing and parmesan. Place chicken and salad on tortilla, roll tightly. Slice in half and serve immediately.

title: Moroccan Vegetable Tagine
description: Fragrant North African stew with chickpeas, root vegetables, and warm spices.
directions: Saute onion 5 minutes. Add cumin, cinnamon, cook 1 minute. Add chopped carrots, sweet potatoes, chickpeas, broth. Simmer 30 minutes until vegetables tender. Season with salt, pepper. Serve over couscous with fresh cilantro.

title: Veggie Buddha Bowl
description: Nourishing bowl with quinoa, roasted vegetables, chickpeas, and tahini dressing.
directions: Cook quinoa. Roast cubed sweet potato and chickpeas with olive oil 25 minutes. Massage kale with lemon juice. Whisk tahini with lemon, water, garlic for dressing. Assemble bowls with quinoa, vegetables, sliced avocado. Drizzle with tahini dressing.

title: Shrimp Scampi
description: Classic Italian-American dish with shrimp in garlic butter white wine sauce over linguine.
directions: Cook linguine al dente. Saute garlic in butter 1 minute. Add shrimp, cook 2 minutes per side. Add wine, lemon juice, simmer 2 minutes. Toss with pasta and parsley. Season with salt, pepper, red pepper flakes. Serve immediately.

title: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Vegetarian version of classic stroganoff with mixed mushrooms in creamy sauce.
directions: Slice mushrooms. Saute onion in butter 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, cook 8 minutes until golden. Add broth, thyme, simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in sour cream. Serve over cooked egg noodles with fresh parsley.

title: Carrot Ginger Soup
description: Silky smooth soup with sweet carrots and warming ginger.
directions: Saute chopped onion 5 minutes. Add sliced carrots and ginger, cook 3 minutes. Add broth, simmer 25 minutes until carrots tender. Blend until smooth. Stir in coconut milk. Season with salt, pepper. Serve with crusty bread.

title: Chicken Quesadilla
description: Crispy tortilla filled with seasoned chicken and melted cheese.
directions: Season and grill chicken, slice thin. Saute peppers and onion. Place tortilla in skillet, add cheese, chicken, vegetables on half. Fold over, cook 2 minutes per side until crispy. Cut into wedges. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: Bruschetta
description: Toasted Italian bread topped with fresh tomato, basil, and garlic mixture.
directions: Dice tomatoes, mix with chopped basil, minced garlic, olive oil, balsamic, salt, pepper. Let marinate 15 minutes. Slice baguette, brush with olive oil, toast until golden. Rub with garlic clove. Top with tomato mixture. Serve immediately.

title: Vegetable Fried Rice
description: Quick stir-fried rice with colorful vegetables and soy sauce.
directions: Use day-old cold rice. Heat oil in wok over high heat. Stir-fry diced carrots 2 minutes. Add peas, garlic, cook 1 minute. Add rice, break up clumps, stir-fry 3 minutes. Add soy sauce, sesame oil. Toss with sliced scallions. Serve hot.

title: Greek Moussaka
description: Layered casserole with eggplant, spiced meat sauce, and creamy bechamel.
directions: Slice and salt eggplant, drain 30 minutes. Fry until golden. Brown lamb with onion, add tomatoes, cinnamon, simmer 20 minutes. Make bechamel with butter, flour, milk. Layer eggplant, meat, bechamel. Bake 180 Celsius 45 minutes until golden.

title: Honey Glazed Carrots
description: Sweet and buttery roasted carrots with honey glaze and fresh herbs.
directions: Peel and cut carrots into sticks. Melt butter in pan, add honey and thyme. Add carrots, toss to coat. Cover and cook 15 minutes until tender. Uncover, cook 5 more minutes until glazed. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

title: Cobb Salad
description: Classic American salad with grilled chicken, bacon, eggs, and blue cheese.
directions: Grill seasoned chicken, slice. Cook bacon until crispy, crumble. Hard boil eggs, quarter. Chop lettuce, arrange on platter. Arrange chicken, bacon, eggs, sliced avocado, halved tomatoes, crumbled blue cheese in rows. Drizzle with ranch dressing.

title: Pumpkin Pie
description: Classic autumn dessert with spiced pumpkin custard in flaky crust.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 Celsius. Whisk pumpkin, eggs, cream, sugar, spices until smooth. Pour into pie crust. Bake 15 minutes, reduce to 180 Celsius, bake 45 minutes until set. Cool completely. Serve with whipped cream.

title: Lemon Garlic Roasted Potatoes
description: Crispy Greek-style potatoes with lemon, garlic, and oregano.
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges. Toss with olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, salt, pepper. Arrange in pan, pour broth around. Roast 200 Celsius 45 minutes until crispy. Squeeze more lemon before serving.

title: Salmon Poke Bowl
description: Hawaiian-inspired bowl with fresh salmon, rice, and tropical toppings.
directions: Cube raw salmon, marinate in soy sauce and sesame oil 15 minutes. Cook rice, cool slightly. Slice cucumber and avocado. Assemble bowls with rice, salmon, vegetables. Top with scallions, sesame seeds, spicy mayo.

title: Vegetable Lasagna
description: Layered pasta with roasted vegetables, ricotta, and marinara sauce.
directions: Cook noodles al dente. Roast sliced zucchini. Mix ricotta with egg, spinach. Layer sauce, noodles, ricotta mixture, vegetables, mozzarella. Repeat layers. Top with parmesan. Bake 180 Celsius 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: Chicken Fried Rice
description: Classic Chinese takeout dish with chicken, vegetables, and scrambled eggs.
directions: Use day-old rice. Cube and cook chicken, set aside. Scramble eggs, set aside. Stir-fry diced carrots and peas. Add rice, soy sauce, toss 3 minutes. Add chicken and eggs. Drizzle sesame oil before serving.

title: Mediterranean Hummus Platter
description: Creamy homemade hummus served with fresh vegetables and warm pita.
directions: Blend chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, olive oil until smooth. Add water for desired consistency. Season with salt, cumin. Spread on plate, drizzle oil, sprinkle paprika. Serve with warm pita and vegetables.

title: Beef Burrito Bowl
description: Deconstructed burrito with seasoned beef, rice, beans, and fresh toppings.
directions: Cook rice with lime juice. Brown beef with taco seasoning. Warm black beans and corn. Assemble bowls with rice, beef, beans, corn. Top with sliced avocado, sour cream, salsa, cheese. Squeeze lime over.

title: Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken
description: Juicy chicken breasts stuffed with creamy spinach and feta cheese.
directions: Mix chopped spinach, feta, cream cheese, garlic. Cut pocket in chicken breasts. Stuff with filling, secure with toothpicks. Sear in olive oil 3 minutes per side. Bake 180 Celsius 20 minutes until cooked through.

title: Thai Green Curry
description: Aromatic coconut curry with vegetables and fragrant Thai herbs.
directions: Heat coconut cream until oil separates. Fry curry paste 2 minutes. Add remaining coconut milk, simmer. Add cubed tofu, peppers, bamboo shoots. Cook 10 minutes. Season with fish sauce, sugar. Garnish with Thai basil. Serve over rice.

title: Stuffed Mushrooms
description: Baked mushroom caps filled with herbed cream cheese and breadcrumbs.
directions: Remove mushroom stems, chop finely. Saute stems with garlic. Mix with cream cheese, parmesan, breadcrumbs, parsley. Fill mushroom caps. Bake 200 Celsius 20 minutes until golden. Serve warm.

title: Honey Soy Glazed Chicken Wings
description: Sticky sweet and savory baked chicken wings with Asian-inspired glaze.
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, garlic, ginger for glaze. Pat wings dry, toss with half the glaze. Bake 200 Celsius 45 minutes, flipping halfway. Brush with remaining glaze, bake 5 more minutes. Sprinkle sesame seeds.

title: Spicy Black Bean Soup
description: Hearty southwestern soup with smoky spices and fresh toppings.
directions: Saute onion and garlic 5 minutes. Add beans, broth, cumin, chili powder. Simmer 20 minutes. Blend half, return to pot. Add lime juice. Serve topped with cilantro, avocado, sour cream.

title: Creamy Tomato Basil Soup
description: Velvety smooth tomato soup with fresh basil and a touch of cream.
directions: Roast halved tomatoes 30 minutes. Saute onion and garlic. Add roasted tomatoes and broth, simmer 15 minutes. Blend until smooth. Stir in cream and chopped basil. Season with salt, pepper. Serve with crusty bread.

title: Mongolian Beef
description: Tender beef slices in sweet and savory sauce with green onions.
directions: Slice beef thin, coat in cornstarch. Fry in hot oil until crispy. Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic, ginger for sauce. Simmer sauce until thick. Toss beef in sauce with sliced scallions. Serve over steamed rice.

title: Vegetable Curry
description: Aromatic Indian curry with mixed vegetables in creamy coconut sauce.
directions: Saute onion and garlic 5 minutes. Add curry powder, cook 1 minute. Add cubed potatoes, cauliflower, water. Simmer 15 minutes. Add peas and coconut milk, cook 10 minutes. Serve over basmati rice with naan.

title: French Onion Soup
description: Rich caramelized onion soup topped with crusty bread and melted gruyere.
directions: Slice onions thin, cook in butter over low heat 45 minutes until caramelized. Add broth and thyme, simmer 20 minutes. Ladle into oven-safe bowls. Top with bread slices and gruyere. Broil until cheese is bubbly and golden.

title: Shrimp Fried Rice
description: Quick stir-fried rice with succulent shrimp and vegetables.
directions: Use cold day-old rice. Cook shrimp 2 minutes per side, set aside. Scramble eggs, set aside. Stir-fry carrots and peas. Add rice, soy sauce, toss 3 minutes. Add shrimp and eggs. Drizzle sesame oil, garnish with scallions.

title: Tuna Salad Sandwich
description: Classic deli-style tuna salad on toasted bread with crisp lettuce.
directions: Drain tuna, flake with fork. Mix with mayo, diced celery, lemon juice, salt, pepper. Toast bread. Spread tuna salad on bread, top with lettuce. Serve with chips or side salad.

title: Chicken Parmesan
description: Breaded chicken cutlets topped with marinara and melted mozzarella.
directions: Pound chicken thin. Dip in egg, then breadcrumbs mixed with parmesan. Fry until golden. Place in baking dish, top with marinara and mozzarella. Bake 200 Celsius 15 minutes until cheese melts. Serve over spaghetti.

title: Roasted Vegetable Medley
description: Colorful mix of seasonal vegetables roasted with herbs and olive oil.
directions: Cut vegetables into chunks. Toss with olive oil, oregano, salt, pepper. Spread on baking sheet. Roast 220 Celsius 25-30 minutes until tender and charred. Squeeze lemon juice before serving.

title: Corn Chowder
description: Creamy soup loaded with sweet corn and tender potatoes.
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add diced potatoes and broth, simmer 15 minutes. Add corn and milk, cook 10 minutes. Blend half for creamier texture. Season with salt, pepper, thyme. Serve with crusty bread.

title: Greek Lamb Gyros
description: Seasoned lamb in warm pita with tzatziki, tomatoes, and onions.
directions: Mix lamb with oregano, garlic, salt, pepper. Form into flat loaf. Bake 180 Celsius 45 minutes. Make tzatziki: grated cucumber, yogurt, garlic. Slice lamb thin. Serve in warm pita with tzatziki, tomatoes, onions.

title: Creamy Mushroom Pasta
description: Fettuccine tossed in rich garlic mushroom cream sauce.
directions: Cook pasta al dente. Saute sliced mushrooms in butter until golden. Add garlic, cook 1 minute. Pour cream, simmer 5 minutes. Add parmesan, stir until melted. Toss with pasta. Season with salt, pepper, fresh thyme.

title: Banana Bread
description: Moist and flavorful quick bread with ripe bananas and optional walnuts.
directions: Mash bananas. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, mashed bananas. Fold in flour, baking soda, salt. Add walnuts if desired. Pour into loaf pan. Bake 175 Celsius 60-65 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: Vegetable Stir Fry
description: Quick and colorful vegetable stir fry in savory sauce.
directions: Heat oil in wok over high heat. Stir-fry carrots 2 minutes. Add broccoli, peppers, snap peas. Cook 3 minutes. Add garlic, ginger, soy sauce. Toss 1 minute until vegetables are crisp-tender. Serve over rice.

title: Chicken Noodle Soup
description: Comforting homemade soup with tender chicken and egg noodles.
directions: Simmer chicken in broth 20 minutes. Remove, shred, set aside. Add diced carrots, celery, onion to broth. Cook 10 minutes. Add noodles, cook 8 minutes. Return chicken to pot. Season with salt, pepper, thyme. Serve hot.

title: Chicken Alfredo
description: Creamy parmesan sauce with grilled chicken over fettuccine.
directions: Season and grill chicken, slice. Cook pasta al dente. Melt butter, saute garlic. Add cream, simmer 5 minutes. Whisk in parmesan until smooth. Toss pasta in sauce, top with chicken. Garnish with parsley and extra parmesan.

title: Blueberry Muffins
description: Fluffy homemade muffins bursting with fresh blueberries.
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt. Combine melted butter, milk, eggs. Fold wet into dry until just combined. Gently fold in blueberries. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 200 Celsius 20-25 minutes until golden.

title: Apple Pie
description: Classic American dessert with spiced apple filling in flaky crust.
directions: Peel and slice apples. Toss with sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg. Line pie dish with crust, fill with apples. Dot with butter, top with second crust. Seal edges, cut vents. Bake 200 Celsius 45-50 minutes until golden.

title: Vegetable Stir Fry
description: A quick and colorful stir-fry with mixed vegetables and a savory sauce. A healthy and delicious vegetarian option.
directions: Heat oil in a large wok or skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and ginger, stir-fry for 30 seconds. Add sliced carrots and bell pepper, cook for 2 minutes. Add broccoli florets and soy sauce, stir-fry for another 3-4 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp. Serve hot over rice or noodles.

title: Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: Classic homemade chocolate chip cookies with a soft center and crispy edges. Perfect for dessert or snacking.
directions: Preheat oven to 175 degrees Celsius. Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. In a separate bowl, whisk flour, baking soda, and salt. Gradually add dry ingredients to wet mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake for 10-12 minutes until edges are golden. Cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to wire rack.

title: Beef Stir Fry
description: Tender beef strips stir-fried with colorful broccoli and bell peppers in a savory soy-garlic sauce. This quick Asian-inspired dish brings bold flavors and crisp textures to your dinner table. Perfect for busy weeknights when you want something healthy and delicious.
directions: Slice beef thinly against the grain. Heat oil in a wok over high heat, stir-fry beef until browned, then remove. In the same wok, stir-fry minced garlic and ginger for 30 seconds, add broccoli and bell pepper, cook until tender-crisp. Return beef to wok, add soy sauce, toss to coat. Serve over rice.

title: Chicken Curry
description: Creamy and aromatic chicken curry simmered in coconut milk with warm spices and tender vegetables. This comforting Indian-inspired dish is rich in flavor and perfect for serving with rice or naan. The blend of spices creates a depth that's both exotic and familiar.
directions: Heat oil in a pot over medium heat. Cook diced onion and minced garlic until softened. Add curry powder and cook for 1 minute. Add cubed chicken, cook until browned. Stir in diced tomatoes and coconut milk, simmer for 20-25 minutes until chicken is tender. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with rice or naan.

title: Pancakes
description: Fluffy homemade pancakes made from scratch with a golden exterior and soft interior. These classic breakfast treats are perfect for stacking high and drizzling with maple syrup. Customize with blueberries or chocolate chips for extra fun.
directions: Whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. In another bowl, beat egg and stir in milk and melted butter. Combine wet and dry ingredients, stir until just mixed. Heat skillet over medium heat, pour batter for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form and edges set, flip and cook until golden. Serve with syrup.

title: Beef Tacos
description: Seasoned ground beef served in soft tortillas with fresh toppings like lettuce, cheese, and salsa. This Mexican favorite is customizable and perfect for family dinners. The combination of spices and fresh ingredients creates a burst of flavor in every bite.
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet over medium-high heat until browned, drain excess fat. Stir in taco seasoning and water, simmer for 5 minutes. Warm tortillas. Fill with seasoned beef, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, and sour cream. Serve with toppings.

title: Mushroom Risotto
description: Creamy Arborio rice slowly cooked with sauteed mushrooms, white wine, and parmesan cheese. This elegant Italian dish requires patience but rewards with luxurious texture and deep flavor. Perfect for special occasions or a comforting weeknight meal.
directions: Heat broth in a saucepan. In a pan, melt butter, saute onion and garlic. Add mushrooms, cook until golden. Stir in rice, cook for 2 minutes. Add wine, stir until absorbed. Gradually add warm broth, stirring until rice is creamy, about 18-20 minutes. Stir in parmesan and butter. Serve.

title: Blueberry Muffins
description: Moist and tender muffins bursting with fresh blueberries and topped with a light sugar crumble. These bakery-style treats are perfect for breakfast or snacking. The combination of sweet berries and buttery batter makes them irresistible.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 Celsius, line muffin tin. Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder. Beat egg, add milk and butter. Combine wet and dry, fold in blueberries. Fill cups, bake 18-20 minutes until toothpick clean. Cool.

title: Vegetable Lasagna
description: Layers of pasta, ricotta cheese, sauteed vegetables, and marinara sauce baked to perfection. This hearty vegetarian dish is packed with nutrients and flavor. It's a great make-ahead meal that feeds a crowd.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 Celsius. Cook lasagna noodles. Saute zucchini and spinach. In a dish, layer sauce, noodles, ricotta, veggies, mozzarella, parmesan. Repeat layers. Bake covered 25 min, uncovered 25 min. Rest before serving.

title: Apple Pie
description: Classic apple pie with a flaky butter crust filled with cinnamon-spiced apples. This all-American dessert is the epitome of comfort food. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream for the ultimate treat.
directions: Preheat oven to 220 Celsius. Peel and slice apples, toss with sugar, cinnamon, flour, lemon juice. Place in pie crust, dot with butter, top with second crust. Bake 45-50 minutes until golden. Cool before serving.

title: Grilled Cheese Sandwich
description: Golden buttered bread filled with melted cheddar cheese, grilled to perfection. This simple comfort food is crispy on the outside and gooey inside. Perfect for a quick lunch or snack with tomato soup.
directions: Butter one side of bread slices. Place cheese between unbuttered sides. Heat skillet over medium heat, cook sandwich buttered side down until golden and cheese melts, flip and cook other side. Serve hot.

title: Beef Stew
description: Slow-simmered beef with potatoes, carrots, and onions in a rich, flavorful broth. This hearty stew is perfect for cold days and develops amazing depth of flavor over time. Serve with crusty bread for soaking up the broth.
directions: Cut beef into cubes. Brown in pot with oil. Sprinkle flour, stir. Add onion, carrots, potatoes, broth, thyme. Bring to boil, simmer covered 1.5-2 hours until tender. Season and serve with bread.

title: Quinoa Salad
description: Nutty quinoa mixed with fresh cucumber, tomatoes, and feta cheese in a light lemon-olive oil dressing. This healthy Mediterranean-inspired salad is refreshing and packed with protein. Perfect for meal prep or as a side dish.
directions: Rinse quinoa, cook in water until absorbed, cool. Dice cucumber and tomatoes. Combine quinoa, veggies, feta, parsley. Whisk oil and lemon juice, pour over, toss. Chill before serving.

title: Chocolate Cake
description: Rich and moist chocolate cake with a deep cocoa flavor, topped with creamy frosting. This indulgent dessert is perfect for celebrations or satisfying chocolate cravings. The cake has a tender crumb and pairs wonderfully with a glass of milk.
directions: Preheat oven to 180 Celsius, grease pans. Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt. Add eggs, milk, oil, vanilla, beat. Stir in boiling water. Bake 30-35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: Egg Fried Rice
description: A quick and flavorful Chinese-inspired dish featuring fluffy rice stir-fried with scrambled eggs, crisp vegetables, and savory soy sauce. This versatile meal is perfect for using leftover rice and can be customized with your favorite veggies. Serve hot as a main or side dish.
directions: Cook rice and let cool. Scramble eggs in oil, set aside. Stir-fry carrots and peas, add rice. Stir in soy sauce, eggs, scallions. Serve hot.

title: Caprese Salad
description: A simple yet elegant Italian salad featuring fresh tomatoes, creamy mozzarella, and fragrant basil drizzled with olive oil and balsamic vinegar. This classic combination highlights the best of summer produce and is perfect as an appetizer or light meal. Season lightly for the purest flavors.
directions: Slice tomatoes and mozzarella into rounds. Arrange alternately on platter, tuck basil leaves. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Let sit to meld flavors.

title: Vegetable Stir Fry
description: A colorful mix of crisp vegetables stir-fried with soy sauce and garlic, served over rice. This quick and healthy dish is packed with nutrients and flavor, perfect for a light dinner or side dish. Customize with your favorite veggies for endless variations.
directions: Heat oil in a wok over high heat. Add minced garlic and ginger, stir-fry for 30 seconds. Add broccoli, bell pepper, carrots, cook until tender-crisp. Stir in soy sauce, toss to coat. Serve over rice.

title: Greek Salad
description: Fresh cucumbers, tomatoes, olives, and feta cheese dressed in olive oil and oregano. This Mediterranean classic is light, refreshing, and full of bold flavors. Perfect as a starter or side dish on a warm day.
directions: Dice cucumber and tomatoes. Crumble feta. Toss with olives. Whisk oil, lemon, oregano. Drizzle over salad, toss. Serve chilled.

title: Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: Chewy and soft cookies loaded with chocolate chips, baked to golden perfection. These classic treats are irresistible and perfect for sharing. Enjoy with a glass of milk for the ultimate comfort snack.
directions: Preheat oven to 175 Celsius. Cream butter and sugars. Beat in egg and vanilla. Mix in flour. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop onto baking sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes until edges golden.

title: Lentil Soup
description: Hearty and nutritious soup made with lentils, vegetables, and spices. This comforting dish is perfect for chilly days and packed with protein. Serve with crusty bread for a satisfying meal.
directions: Saute onion, garlic, carrots in pot. Add lentils, tomato, cumin, broth. Simmer 25-30 minutes until lentils tender. Season and serve.

title: Beef Tacos
description: Flavorful tacos with seasoned ground beef, fresh vegetables, and cheese.
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with chopped onion and minced garlic. Stir in taco seasoning and cook until beef is done. Warm tortillas. Fill with beef mixture, shredded lettuce, diced tomato, and cheese. Serve immediately.

title: Vegetable Curry
description: Spicy and aromatic curry with mixed vegetables and coconut milk.
directions: Saute chopped onion, minced garlic, and grated ginger in a pan. Add mixed vegetables and curry powder, stir to coat. Pour in vegetable broth, bring to simmer. Cook for 15-20 minutes until vegetables are tender. Stir in coconut milk and heat through. Serve with rice.

title: Grilled Cheese Sandwich
description: Classic comfort food with melted cheese between toasted bread.
directions: Butter one side of each bread slice. Place cheese slices between bread, add sliced tomato and onion. Heat skillet over medium heat. Grill sandwich until bread is golden and cheese is melted, about 3-4 minutes per side.

title: Chicken Stir Fry
description: Quick and healthy stir fry with chicken and mixed vegetables.
directions: Heat vegetable oil in wok or skillet. Stir fry cubed chicken breast until cooked. Add minced garlic, ginger, broccoli florets, and sliced bell pepper. Stir in soy sauce and cook for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp. Serve over rice.

title: Pancakes
description: Fluffy breakfast pancakes served with syrup and butter.
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, and sugar in a bowl. In another bowl, whisk milk, egg, and melted butter. Combine wet and dry ingredients until just mixed. Heat griddle over medium heat. Pour batter to form pancakes. Cook until bubbles form and edges look set, then flip and cook until golden. Serve with syrup.

title: Spaghetti Bolognese
description: Classic Italian pasta dish with rich meat sauce.
directions: Heat olive oil in pot. Saute chopped onion, minced garlic, and diced carrot. Add ground beef and cook until browned. Stir in tomato sauce and simmer for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, boil spaghetti according to package. Drain and toss with sauce. Serve with grated cheese.

title: Quinoa Salad
description: Healthy and refreshing salad with quinoa, fresh vegetables, and lemon dressing.
directions: Cook quinoa according to package instructions and let cool. Dice cucumber, tomato, and onion. Chop parsley. In a bowl, mix quinoa with vegetables and parsley. Whisk lemon juice and olive oil for dressing. Toss salad with dressing and season to taste.

title: Chocolate Brownies
description: Rich and fudgy chocolate brownies perfect for dessert.
directions: Preheat oven to 175 Celsius. Melt butter and mix with sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Sift in flour, cocoa, and baking powder. Stir until combined. Pour into greased pan. Bake for 25-30 minutes until set. Cool before cutting.

title: Salmon Teriyaki
description: Grilled salmon fillets glazed with sweet and savory teriyaki sauce.
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, minced garlic, ginger, and sesame oil for marinade. Marinate salmon for 30 minutes. Preheat grill or oven to 200 Celsius. Cook salmon for 10-12 minutes, basting with marinade. Garnish with chopped green onions. Serve with rice.

title: Caprese Salad
description: Simple and elegant Italian salad with fresh tomatoes, mozzarella, and basil.
directions: Slice tomatoes and mozzarella. Arrange on plate with basil leaves. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Sprinkle with minced garlic. Season with salt and pepper. Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: Shrimp Scampi
description: Garlic butter shrimp served over linguine with lemon and parsley.
directions: Cook linguine according to package. In skillet, melt butter and saute minced garlic. Add shrimp and cook until pink. Stir in white wine and lemon juice, simmer for 2 minutes. Toss cooked pasta with shrimp mixture and chopped parsley. Serve immediately.

title: Thai Green Curry
description: Spicy and aromatic Thai curry with coconut milk and vegetables.
directions: Heat curry paste in a pan. Add garlic and ginger, stir. Pour in coconut milk and bring to simmer. Add cubed tofu and vegetables. Cook for 10-15 minutes. Stir in soy sauce. Serve with rice.

title: Caesar Salad
description: Classic salad with romaine lettuce, croutons, and Caesar dressing.
directions: Chop lettuce. Toss with croutons, parmesan, and dressing. Squeeze lemon and add minced garlic. Mix well and serve.

title: Blueberry Muffins
description: Sweet muffins bursting with fresh blueberries.
directions: Mix dry ingredients. In another bowl, whisk milk, egg, melted butter. Combine, fold in blueberries. Fill muffin tin. Bake at 190 Celsius for 20-25 minutes.

title: Tuna Salad
description: Simple and refreshing tuna salad with mayonnaise.
directions: Drain tuna. Mix with mayonnaise, diced celery, chopped onion, lemon juice, and salt. Chill and serve on bread or lettuce.

title: Lasagna
description: Layered pasta dish with meat sauce and cheese.
directions: Cook noodles. Brown beef with onion and garlic. Layer noodles, meat sauce, ricotta, mozzarella. Repeat layers. Bake at 190 Celsius for 30 minutes.

title: Apple Pie
description: Classic pie with spiced apple filling.
directions: Peel and slice apples. Mix with sugar, cinnamon, flour. Place in pie crust, dot with butter. Top with second crust. Bake at 220 Celsius for 45 minutes.

title: Lemon Garlic Chicken Thighs
description: Juicy roasted chicken thighs with a bright lemon-garlic glaze.
directions: Preheat oven and whisk lemon juice, oil, garlic, oregano, and pepper. Pat chicken dry and brush with the marinade, then roast until cooked through and skin is crisp. Baste once during cooking and let rest 5 minutes before serving. Serve with pan juices spooned over the top.

title: Honey Soy Salmon Bowl
description: Quick glazed salmon served over rice and crisp veggies.
directions: Whisk soy and honey into a glaze and brush over salmon. Pan-sear or bake the salmon until caramelized and just cooked through, basting with glaze. Steam or saute snap peas until crisp-tender. Assemble bowls with rice, salmon, and vegetables, finishing with sliced green onion.

title: Peanut Butter Banana Smoothie
description: Creamy smoothie with peanut butter and banana for a quick boost.
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until very smooth. Taste and add honey if additional sweetness is desired. Pour into a glass and enjoy immediately for best texture.

title: Maple Glazed Carrots
description: Sweet and savory roasted carrots glazed with maple.
directions: Toss carrots with oil, maple, butter (if using), and thyme. Roast until tender and edges caramelize, stirring once. Drizzle any pan glaze over before serving. Serve warm as a sweet-savory side.

title: Chicken Caesar Wrap
description: Grilled chicken wrapped with crisp romaine and Caesar flavors.
directions: Toss sliced chicken with lettuce, dressing, parmesan, and crushed croutons. Lay mixture on a tortilla and roll tightly, folding in the ends. Slice in half and serve immediately. Wraps travel well for lunches.

title: Turkey & Quinoa Stuffed Peppers
description: Bell peppers stuffed with savory turkey and quinoa mixture.
directions: Saute onion and turkey until browned, stir in quinoa and tomato sauce and simmer briefly. Spoon the mixture into prepared peppers and top with mozzarella. Bake until peppers are tender and cheese is melted. Let cool slightly before serving.

title: Creamy Mushroom Pasta
description: Silky mushroom sauce tossed with pasta for a comforting bowl.
directions: Cook pasta until al dente and reserve some cooking water. Saute garlic and mushrooms in butter until browned, add cream and simmer to thicken. Stir in parmesan and toss with pasta, adding cooking water as needed to loosen the sauce. Serve immediately with extra cheese.

title: Garlic Butter Shrimp Skewers
description: Quick skewered shrimp basted with a garlic butter glaze.
directions: Thread shrimp onto skewers and season lightly. Melt butter with garlic and lemon juice, then brush over shrimp before grilling. Grill briefly on each side until opaque and just cooked. Brush again with garlic butter and sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: Baked Cinnamon Pears
description: Warm baked pears with a honey-cinnamon glaze and nutty topping.
directions: Place pears cut-side up in a baking dish and dot with butter. Drizzle honey and sprinkle cinnamon over each half, then scatter walnuts. Bake until pears are tender and caramelized around the edges. Serve warm with a spoonful of yogurt or cream.

title: Lemon Herb Shrimp Pasta
description: Bright lemon and herb tossed with shrimp and pasta for a light dinner.
directions: Cook pasta and reserve some cooking water. Saute garlic and shrimp in oil until shrimp turn pink, add lemon and parsley. Toss with pasta, adding reserved water to loosen if needed. Serve with extra lemon zest.

title: Vegetable Stir Fry
description: A quick and healthy stir fry with colorful vegetables and a savory soy ginger sauce.
directions: Chop all vegetables into bite-sized pieces. Heat sesame oil in a wok over high heat. Add garlic and ginger, stir for 30 seconds. Add vegetables and stir-fry for 5-7 minutes until tender-crisp. Pour in soy sauce and toss to coat. Serve hot over rice.

title: Caprese Salad
description: Simple and elegant Italian salad with fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, and basil.
directions: Slice tomatoes and mozzarella into rounds. Arrange alternately on a platter. Tuck fresh basil leaves between slices. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: Green Curry Chicken
description: Spicy Thai green curry with tender chicken and bamboo shoots.
directions: Slice chicken into thin strips. Heat a pot over medium heat and fry the curry paste for 1 minute. Add coconut milk and bring to a simmer. Add chicken and bamboo shoots. Simmer for 10-15 minutes until chicken is cooked. Stir in fish sauce and basil leaves.

title: Spaghetti Carbonara
description: Roman pasta dish made with egg, hard cheese, cured pork, and black pepper.
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente. While pasta cooks, fry chopped bacon until crisp. Whisk eggs and cheese together. Drain pasta, reserving some water. off heat, toss pasta with bacon fat and egg mixture quickly to create a creamy sauce. Add pasta water if needed. Season generously with pepper.

title: Banana Bread
description: Moist and sweet quick bread made with ripe mashed bananas.
directions: Preheat oven to 175 Celsius. Mash bananas. Mix melted butter and sugar, then beat in egg and mashed bananas. Stir in baking soda and salt. Gently fold in flour. Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake for 60 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: Quinoa Salad
description: Light and fluffy quinoa tossed with cucumber, tomato, and lemon vinaigrette.
directions: Rinse and cook quinoa according to package instructions; let cool. Dice cucumber and halve tomatoes. In a large bowl, combine quinoa, vegetables, and chopped parsley. Whisk lemon juice and olive oil, pour over salad, and toss.

title: Gazpacho
description: Refreshing cold tomato soup from Spain.
directions: Roughly chop all vegetables. Blend tomatoes, cucumber, pepper, onion, and garlic until smooth. Stir in olive oil and vinegar. Season with salt. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: Eggplant Parmesan
description: Layers of breaded eggplant, marinara sauce, and melted cheese.
directions: Slice eggplant, dip in beaten egg, then breadcrumbs. Bake or fry slices until golden. In a baking dish, layer eggplant, marinara sauce, and cheeses. Bake at 190 Celsius for 25-30 minutes until bubbly.

title: Beef Stroganoff
description: Tender beef strips in a rich sour cream and mushroom sauce.
directions: Saute sliced beef in butter until browned; remove. Saute onions and mushrooms. Stir in flour, then add broth and simmer. Return beef to pan. Stir in sour cream and heat through without boiling. Serve over noodles.

title: Falafel Wrap
description: Crispy chickpea balls wrapped in pita with veggies and tahini.
directions: Blend soaked chickpeas, herbs, and spices. Form into balls and fry until golden. Spread tahini on warm pita, add lettuce and falafel, and roll up.

title: Shrimp Scampi
description: Succulent shrimp cooked in a buttery garlic and lemon sauce.
directions: Saute garlic in butter. Add shrimp and cook until pink. Pour in wine and lemon juice, simmer for 2 minutes. Garnish with parsley and serve over pasta or with crusty bread.

title: Cobb Salad
description: Mixed greens topped with chicken, bacon, avocado, egg, and blue cheese.
directions: Grill chicken and chop. Cook bacon until crisp and crumble. Boil eggs and slice. Arrange lettuce on a platter. Top with rows of chicken, bacon, avocado slices, egg, cheese, and diced tomato. Serve with vinaigrette.

title: Ratatouille
description: Vegetable stew from Provence with zucchini, eggplant, and peppers.
directions: Dice all vegetables. Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add peppers and eggplant, cook for 5 minutes. Add zucchini and tomatoes. Season with thyme, salt, and pepper. Simmer covered for 20-30 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: Apple Pie
description: Classic dessert with spiced apples in a flaky crust.
directions: Preheat oven to 190 Celsius. Peel and slice apples; toss with sugar, flour, and cinnamon. Line pie plate with one crust. Fill with apples and dot with butter. Top with second crust, seal edges, and cut slits. Bake for 45-50 minutes until golden.

title: Shakshuka
description: Eggs poached in a sauce of tomatoes, chili peppers, and onions.
directions: Saute chopped onion and bell pepper until soft. Add garlic and spices. Stir in chopped tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes to thicken. Make wells in the sauce and crack eggs into them. Cover and cook until eggs are set. Serve with crusty bread.

title: Guacamole
description: Creamy avocado dip with lime, onion, and cilantro.
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl. Stir in diced onion, tomato, jalapeno, cilantro, and lime juice. Season with salt. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: Hummus
description: Smooth chickpea dip with tahini and lemon.
directions: Process garlic, tahini, and lemon juice in a food processor. Add chickpeas, cumin, and olive oil. Blend until smooth, adding water if needed for consistency. Serve with pita bread.

title: Pancakes
description: Fluffy breakfast cakes served with syrup.
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Whisk milk, egg, and melted butter; pour into dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Pour batter onto a hot greased griddle. Flip when bubbles form. Serve with maple syrup.

title: Bruschetta
description: Toasted bread topped with tomato and basil mixture.
directions: Dice tomatoes and mix with chopped basil, minced garlic, olive oil, and vinegar. Let sit. Slice baguette and toast. Top warm bread with tomato mixture.

title: Beef Burrito
description: Flour tortilla filled with seasoned beef, rice, and beans.
directions: Cook rice. Brown ground beef with taco seasoning. Warm tortillas. Layer rice, beans, beef, cheese, and salsa on each tortilla. Fold in sides and roll up tight.

title: Spinach Artichoke Dip
description: Creamy cheesy dip with spinach and artichoke hearts.
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Chop artichokes. Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Transfer to a baking dish. Bake at 190 Celsius for 20-25 minutes until bubbly and golden. Serve with chips.

title: Pumpkin Soup
description: Smooth and velvety soup made with roasted pumpkin.
directions: Saute onion and garlic. Add pumpkin puree, broth, and spices. Simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in coconut milk. Blend if needed for smoother consistency. Serve warm.

title: Shepherd's Pie
description: Ground meat pie with a crust of mashed potato.
directions: Boil and mash potatoes with butter. Brown meat with chopped onion and carrots. Add broth and peas, simmer until thickened. Transfer to baking dish, top with mashed potatoes. Bake at 200 Celsius for 25 minutes.

title: Chia Seed Pudding
description: Healthy pudding made with chia seeds and almond milk.
directions: Whisk chia seeds, milk, syrup, and vanilla in a jar. Let sit for 5 minutes, whisk again. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight. Top with berries before serving.

title: Potato Salad
description: Creamy salad made with boiled potatoes and mayonnaise.
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, drain and cool. hard boil eggs. Chop potatoes and eggs. Mix with diced celery, onion, mayo, and mustard. Chill before serving.

title: Italian Meatballs
description: Juicy beef and pork meatballs simmered in marinara sauce.
directions: Mix beef, breadcrumbs, cheese, egg, and parsley. Form into balls. Bake at 200 Celsius for 15-20 minutes. Simmer in marinara sauce for 10 minutes. Serve over pasta.

title: Chocolate Brownies
description: Fudgy and rich chocolate squares.
directions: Melt butter. Stir in sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Stir in cocoa and flour. Pour into greased square pan. Bake at 165 Celsius for 20-25 minutes.

title: Minestrone Soup
description: Thick Italian soup made with vegetables and pasta.
directions: Saute chopped carrots and celery. Add diced tomatoes and broth. Simmer for 15 minutes. Add beans and pasta. Cook until pasta is tender. Stir in spinach.

title: Moussaka
description: Layered casserole with eggplant, spiced meat sauce, and bechamel.
directions: Slice and fry eggplant. Cook meat sauce. Make bechamel. Layer eggplant, meat, bechamel. Bake until golden.
